notes: Previous guests have shared in our guest book that the guest house has a "soothing feeling." Many have come for "one night", but stayed for many more. Artists come for inspiration, musicians stop over during tours, writers return because of the "creative energy," & families love the atmosphere and access...uu
transit: Located in mid-town Santa Cruz, you can walk to much of our community's great features. The bus stop is 2 blocks away. Bikes are perfect way to get around.
host_about:
We are empty nesters who spend our free time outside, exploring, and being active. Walks along the coast and hiking are our main activities. We love Santa Cruz for it's funky free spirit, vibrant vitality, diverse community, and its central location to countless other areas—San Francisco, Monterey, Carmel, Big Sur, Highway 1, Yosemite, and Tahoe, among other amazing places!

We have been hosting guests for 8 years via word of mouth and are excited to now open it up to all travelers. We love sharing our back house and community with others, and hope to provide a welcoming atmosphere that will make your stay perfect.

space: Design lovers and surfers, welcome home! Each piece of furniture in this house was curated to be not only beautiful but also functional and comfortable. You'll love the modern, open design and how it's just a two minute walk from Pleasure Point. Surf the world famous waves at The Hook, and then relax a few minutes later back at home. This amazing 1,680 sq ft home includes 3 bedrooms (+loft with sleeper sofa), 2 full baths, soaring ceilings in the living room, a roof deck with ocean view, a front deck for people watching and dining, and a side deck for grilling. neighborhood_overview: Our home is located in the quiet Pleasure Point neighborhood away from the noise of downtown.  It's just two minutes to some of the best surfing breaks in Northern California at Pleasure Point, Diamonds, Sharks, The Hook, and 38th Street. You can take a quick 10 minute stroll up the water to the private Moran beach or enjoy walking around the quiet neighborhood. You'll catch locals walking down to the water with surfboards in hand, skateboarding, and walking their dogs. A ten minute walk or 2 minute drive to 41st Ave has the famous Pleasure Pizza and Penny Ice Creamery. Nearby Capitola has charming restaurants and bars including Shadowbrook. Nisene Marks Redwood Forest is nearby for great trail biking, hiking, and running. The famous Santa Cruz boardwalk is ten minutes west where you can enjoy the beach, amusement park, and restaurants such as Picnic Basket. Safeway, Target, Whole Foods, and New Leaf are all nearby on 41st Ave within a ten minute drive.
notes: We require a 3 night minimum.
transit: The spacious driveway can fit up to 4 cars. There are restaurants, bars, and markets within 10 minutes walking distance. At the end of the street, a paved walking/biking path runs along the coast.
host_about:
We personally design and love our homes, but we don't always get to use them.  We hope we can open our homes to you and share the experience.

We love art, architecture, surfing, and hiking and typically spend time in San Francisco, Santa Cruz, New York City, and Tokyo.

neighborhood_overview: Branciforte drive is just slightly outside of downtown Santa Cruz. Once you figure out the streets, you will realize you are actually only 5-10 minutes from downtown and the beaches, but in a quieter and more peaceful setting.The house location is at the very beginning of Branciforte Drive, about 2 miles before the Mystery Spot, and directly across the street from a very popular trailhead at DeLaVeaga Park. It is also a popular bike ride with local road bikers, so bring a bike if you like to ride.
notes: Sometimes Branciforte Drive can seem very busy with cars, as the Mystery Spot is a popular destination, but a very safe and easy turn around  is just a few seconds past the house at the "Mystery Spot 2 Miles" sign.
host_about: I have lived in Pleasure Point for  over twenty years and I love it!! I am very active, and love being a block from the ocean, as well as within biking distance to some epic trail rides in the Santa cruz mountains. I have travelled all over the world, and I always love coming home to my sweet little neighborhood by the beach:)

name: Beautiful home by UCSC and Beaches
summary: This lovely  cottage plus detached guest room puts you in the sought-after location of sunny upper Westside in a quiet neighborhood on a dead-end street. Stroll to the end of the road into a state park and into the redwoods. Excellent mtn. biking right out the door.  Little over a mile from the beach and downtown. Located at the base of UCSC. Private, fenced big yard with BBQ.
space: Our space is a unique quiet Oasis. It's always sunny on the Upper Westside and there is usually a gentle refreshing breeze to enjoy as you sit in the back yard surrounded by apple, pear, and lemon tree. It's quiet, peaceful  home to come back to after adventuring at Roaring Camp Railroad, running around the Boardwalk, or hiking all day in Wilder Ranch.  We cherish it dearly and hope you will love it as much as we do! We both grew up in Santa Cruz surfing and riding bikes and can answer any questions re bike rentals, trails, places to hike, beaches to go to etc. It's a wonderful place full of everything to do with great restaurants and down town close by! Each bedroom in the house has a deluxe queen size bed made up with high quality linens, down comforters and pillows. The newly built detached room in the back of the yard  has a high quality very comfortable stacked twin sleeper that unfolds to an oversized queen bed. My guests say they prefer it over their beds at home!

neighborhood_overview: Very quiet neighborhood, friendly, and always sunny! Even when the fog is at the beach. This is our private home we are renting and ask that you cherish it as we do. We are friends with our neighbors and respect their appreciation of quiet and privacy. Be mindful of the 10 o'clock noise curfew. If you are outside having drinks on the deck or having a fire, just lower your voices after 10.
notes: Backyard chickens enclosed in charming coop and run in far corner of back yard. Chickens are quiet and provide fresh eggs daily that you may help yourself to. We get about 4 a day. Please pick  and enjoy as many organic apples, pears, plums and lemons off our trees! Fees to be collected prior to check in 11% transit occupancy tax  25 per pet/day 25/person/day after 4 guests 50 late check out fee per hr
transit: There is a bus stop 1 block away.

name: Riverside Ranch: Sun Stucco
space: Hi there. I have a really special space to share in a wonderful, convenient location. This 1930's two bedroom stucco is located on a multi-home property on a quiet residential street just a few minutes walk from downtown, the Boardwalk, and Main Beach. You can hear the sound of the waves when the wind blows just right. Sunny and bright, the house sits on a large lot, set back from the street. The lot is shared with another two other rentals (Simple Studio and Lil Loafer) as well as two occupied houses.  Sun Stucco is creamy white, clean, airy and stylishly decorated. It features refinished wood floors, original tile work in the kitchen and a bath and outdoor patio area. The light in this house is fantastic! You feel like you are in an old movie set in Palm Springs.  The people living on the property are writers, academics, designers, teachers. There is a eight year old living on the property as well. Kid friendly! Old dogs welcomed.

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is a quiet steer right in the middle of everything. Just over the bridge (10 min walk?) is downtown. If you head the opposite direction you will find the Boardwalk and the beach.
host_about:
Hello, my name is Charlotte and I am excited to be a host for Airbnb. I love meeting new people and look forward to hosting folks coming through town. I live right next door to this rental with my adorable Jack Russell, Jerry Lee, so I will be available and nearby if you have any questions. 

I am a textile artist and own my own small business called Stand West, where I design and hand make a range of luxury, eco conscious accessories using custom dyed fabrics and mostly repurposed materials. If you are extra curious check out @standwestcreations on Instagram. 

In addition to Stand West I am a Hip Hop Dance Teacher and work with Crush Sunglasses (a company based in the LA area) as their Northern California lifestyle rep. 

Despite growing up in beautiful Colorado and having the opportunity to explore every state in the USA, Santa Cruz has a strong hold on my heart. Here I spend the majority of my free time at the skate park located just a few blocks from Riverside Ranch, running on West Cliff, visiting the farmers markets that are held every day of the week throughout town, taking my dog to the beach, hiking in the redwoods with friends, and working with the community to make this city even better then it already is. 

I have been blessed beyond my own imagination to travel many places across the globe through the benefits of having  a mother as a Airline Stewardess. Because of all of my experiences being away from home I have a huge heart for making sure that your stay is the best it can be. Staying somewhere that feels like home, rather then in a hotel, makes all of the difference for me when I am exploring new places. Thank God for Airbnb. ; ) 

I hope to have the chance to get to know you and whether or not you decide to stay at Riverside Ranch I'll be wishing for you the best experiences while you are here in Santa Cruz. 

Light and Love!

Charlie

When possible we ask that you park in the cul de sac due to oil stain
neighborhood_overview: We live in a small neighborhood court.  Our home backs to open space which creates a more private quiet setting away from the  main road and  offers bird watching fun. Privacy and lovely views.   There is a park/tennis court  next door as well as several restaurants just steps away.  Harbor Beach Café is a popular breakfast spot, and Crows Nest Restaurant is a popular all around fun spot day and night.   Twin Lakes Beach is a 10 to 15 minute walk and one of the most popular beaches in Santa Cruz do to it's great location and easy access. Additionally there are several nature trails in the area; and the Santa Cruz harbor is walking distance as well!    :-)
notes: As a Certified Massage Practitioner, I will make myself available should you desire some pampering as timing allows.  45/ hour in home. We have a small Pomerian pup that we keep with us as much as possible
transit: There is a bus stop close by on 7th avenue, but you can walk  to beach, park restaurants, harbor and hiking trails from our home easily!  The location can't be beat.
host_about: Family oriented nature lover with sense of adventure, social and welcoming!

space: 1887 Victorian Historical Landmark on Beach Hill. Beautiful 4br/2ba on upper level of Eastlake style duplex.  Approximately 1900 square feet of space. neighborhood_overview: Located on the upper West Side of Santa Cruz, between the UCSC campus and the beach, Mahalo Cottage is surrounded by some of the best restaurants, surf shops, hiking, coffee shops, wine tasting rooms and bakeries that Santa Cruz has to offer--all within walking distance. We also have 2 FREE guest access passes to the Monterey Bay Aquarium! (We only ask that you return the passes after your visit.)
notes: Make this a true retreat! If you are looking for help with challenges in life, or just a way to go more deeply into your own spiritual nature, on-site coaching is available from Ami, who is a global teacher and author of books on simple, spiritual principles that have now helped thousands regain the birthright of their innate well-being and natural wisdom. Please call (phone number hidden) to arrange this as part of your stay.
transit: The Santa Cruz metro bus provides fast and easy transportation around town, and access is located steps away. A walk to the beach is about 20 minutes, and it is an easy downhill walk to groceries, restaurants, wineries, coffee shops--but then you must be prepared to walk back uphill! :)

space: West Cliff Drive is the premier spot on the NorCal coast to walk, people watch, surf, bike, and enjoy spectacular sunsets. We are also minutes to the famed Santa Cruz Boardwalk with rides and nightlife, great west side restaurants, wineries and bistros a 5 minute bikeride away, and funky downtown with book stores, old movie houses and coffee shops. Our peaceful oasis by the sea is a great place enjoy the sound of ocean by night and two nice swimming beaches a short walk . The owner is an artist in process of renovating the main mid-century house on the property. Watch the garden grow and site come alive again each time you visit! neighborhood_overview: People, people, community, surrounded by the magnificent ocean and all her sealife...WestCliff drive is the hub of Santa Cruz, with bicyclists, walkers, surfers and pelicans flying around to add to the mix. One hears all languages on a walk: we are a university town with lots of interesting people mixing with the locals.
notes: Due to the severe  drought in California, we ask guests to please limit shower time and in general observe the local laws regarding water conservation. Thank you in advance.
transit: Bus runs one block away to all over town. We got some beach cruiser bikes which can get you downtown and just about anywhere in Santa Cruz, including the boardwalk where the famous amusement park is.
host_about: I am an artist, working on environmental issues.  We've got a dog and some teenage girls running around the place. We have returned from central europe, after many years abroad, so you may hear us speaking a funny language that barely has vowels.  I still cannot believe that we've landed in this glorious spot on the planet, surrounded by dolphins and the great Pacific at our doorstep. Feeling blessed!

I'm a Licensed Clinical Social Worker specializing in child abuse and neglect and East Coast transplant (Rochester, New York) but since 1995 have considered California my home. I am regularly at the beach playing volleyball or out on my boat enjoying the water. Chris is also a LCSW who specializes in mental illness and an award winning artist whose large are  abstract paintings displayed throughout the house. We love to cook, enjoy a libation and listen to live music: to entertain and be entertained! 
We are fortunate to travel internationally often but we always love coming back to Santa Cruz.

name: Yacht Harbor 1 Block to Seabright
summary: Charming Carmel style 3 bedroom, 2 ½ bathroom two story located 1 ½ blocks from beach on 1st Avenue. Staying here is more of an enjoyable, walkable, beach vacation close to food and Boardwalk. 7 night minimum. Will NOT respond to less than 7 nights.
space: The house is 5 years old, like new and furnished. It was designed with open family room kitchen, bedroom (2 twin beds) and full bath on first floor with gas fireplace. Second floor has 2 bedrooms (one full, one queen bed), 1 bath, half bath and laundry closet.  You'll be only a few blocks to the Seabright Beach, with its white sands and crowd free beach, then keep walking through to the Santa Cruz Yacht Harbor, Seabright Brewery, Day's Market, Engfer Pizza Works Wood Fired Pizzas, Betty Burgers, La Posta Italian Restaurant, and Tramonti Wood Fired Pizza . Or stop for breakfast at Linda's Seabreeze Cafe, Then head on down to the beach, or walk to the yacht harbor, or check out the lighthouse at the end of Seabright beach.  Close by activities include the famous Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk. The Yacht harbor offers kayaking, paddle boarding, afternoon boat trip on The Chardonnay or meal at Aldo's or Crow's Nest.   RENTAL FEATURES 1 ½ blocks to beach Radiant floor heat Gas fireplace One car

neighborhood_overview: The Seabright neighborhood itself is an attraction.  Whether you’re gazing from the upper deck or strolling,  there are several points of interest.  This is a good and safe place to walk or ride a bicycle.  Go north along E. Cliff Dr., toward the San Lorenzo River to the “Point” where you can look across the river toward the Boardwalk, the Santa Cruz Wharf,  the Steamer Lane Museum Lighthouse, back toward Walton Lighthouse and Seabright beach.  Wander the neighborhood and you’ll see little late 19th and early 20th century summer cottages in various styles and unique contemporary bungalows. Seabright Beach, sometimes called “Castle Beach” for the former “mansion” sitting at what is now the main entrance, is 100 steps from the our vacation rental house.  The beach stretches ½ mile from Walton lighthouse, situated at the mouth of the breakwater entrance to the Yacht Harbor, to the San Lorenzo River mouth next to the Boardwalk. host_about:
I am eternally optimistic:)

I work from the belief that life should be fun. Even when life throws curve balls, the question is how you handle them? I try to be playful with most everything that comes my way. If I am not having a good time, whose fault is that? Obviously not everything in life is within our control and for those things we do have control over, then we have choices to make. Do we choose to enjoy what life has to offer? I try as much as my presence of mind is able. I am kind and generous; perhaps too much so at times according to my friends. I find that expressing compassion, understanding, and forgiveness has brought me “rewards” beyond my wildest imagination. I am honored to have you all as my friends. Peace. pp

neighborhood_overview: We think this is the best neighborhood in Santa Cruz because of its central location!  You would be able to enjoy lots of attractions with or without a car here.  Just a 10 minute walk to restaurants, the Rio Theater, and shopping.  Whole Foods, Shoppers Corner and The Buttery (the best bakery in town) are a few blocks away.  Downtown and the wharf are a 25-30 min walk or a 7 minute drive.  UCSC, Capitola Village, and hiking in the Redwoods are all within a 10 minute drive as well.
notes: Two things to note about our property: 1)  We have a large, and VERY friendly dog.  We will try to keep her out of your way, but she will likely want to pay you a visit and is roaming the yard frequently.  If you stay here, we hope you like dogs! 2)  We have a chicken coop with 8, beautiful laying hens next to the guesthouse.  We think the chickens are lots of fun to watch, and are particularly fun if you have children.  Kids love to feed the chickens, and ours are very friendly.  Hens don't make nearly as much noise as roosters, but they do like to chatter and occasionally squawk.  We are not bothered by the noise and think it is a nice soft sound, but please be aware that you will hear the chickens. Also-- Santa Cruz charges an 11% occupancy tax.  For your convenience, we have included this charge in the nightly rate.
transit: Parking is very easy on the street in front of our house, and we are also walking distance to a bus.

neighborhood_overview: Perched directly across from the ocean and the Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary Visitor's Center. Take the free summertime trolley offering service to downtown Santa Cruz with a stop outside your front door. Walk to the lighthouse museum at Lighthouse Field or hop on the old fashion locomotive train to Roaring Camp Redwoods. Enjoy 30+ restaurants and shops, rent surfboards, watch the whales and dolphins, enjoy the boardwalk or retreat on your own private deck with fantastic ocean views.
notes: PLEASE NOTE, the City of Santa Cruz has an 11% Occupancy tax which will be added to your booking. Inquire about the Penthouse which features a 1500 square foot outdoor living space with full outdoor kitchen, which could be combined to with your villa to make the ultimate vacation. The Sea Crest is largest villa with commanding views, 4 bedrooms and 4 bathrooms with 3 master suites, kids room with dual bunk beds and features a 14 foot long kitchen island with bar seating for 7. The Monarch boasts 4 bedrooms with 3 bathrooms, enormous master suite, 2 king size beds, kids room with dual bunk beds, 3 soaking tubs, ocean views, and a deluxe gourmet kitchen.
transit: Truly no need for a car once you arrive. Bike and surfboard rental offered on the same block. Walking distance to wharf, West Cliff, Boardwalk, Cowells Beach, Downtown, Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary Center, and dozens of restaurants and shops.  Downtown Trolley Runs across the street during the summer, and Public bus runs year round.

neighborhood_overview: Our spacious downtown vacation home is great for any occasion-- whether you want to spend a few days at the beach with your family, go hiking in the beautiful redwood forests our town has to offer, ride the Giant Dipper and enjoy a funnel cake at the Boardwalk, see the monarch butterflies nest at Natural Bridges State Park, have the perfect weekend getaway with your special someone, get a seafood dinner with an ocean view on the wharf, take a stroll down the beautiful backdrop of West Cliff Dr., or would just like enjoy some peace and quiet in a serene environment-- you've come to the right place! Walk to the farmers market  on Wednesdays and make yourself a gourmet meal in the large fully equipped kitchen. Everything we mentioned is in walking distance, you wouldn't even need to rent a car! The home is located in the heart of downtown Santa Cruz, but you wouldn't even know it! So peaceful and serene, it is extremely quiet, so much so, if you listen hard enough you can sometimes hear t
notes: Per Santa Cruz City law, we are required as Airbnb hosts to collect the Transient Occupancy Tax (TOT) separately from your Airbnb transaction. The TOT is 11% of the nightly rate (before fees) for each night you stay. As this is a city tax, we are not allowed to collect this through Airbnb. We will collect this in cash or check upon check-in or during checkout. **********************  Check in is at 4PM  **********************  Check out is at 11AM  **********************  For guests that are planning on going to The Boardwalk:  Consider staying with us on a Monday or a Tuesday, as the Boardwalk has 1.00 rides, hot dogs, cotton candy & soda from 5PM to closing. It's a great bargain and tons of fun!  We offer an airport pickup and drop-off from SJO or SFO for an extra fee. Please let us know in advance if this is something you're interested in. The house is separated into two different units, an upstairs and a downstairs. They are completely private from each other, with two separate en
transit: Walking and biking is the best way to appreciate the Santa Cruz scenery.  However, car rental services are available. There is a bus station on Pacific Ave. but there are many bus stops closer to your home away from home. The Metro Bus Station is where both local buses and Greyhound buses depart from. The Santa Cruz Trolley loops around Pacific Ave. and goes to the wharf and Boardwalk for only 25 cents! You can rent segway scooters down the street from the Boardwalk to use in that area. Information regarding rental services will be included in our information pamphlet, or emailed upon request. We do have a single parking driveway, and allot 1 guest pass for the permitted street parking.  A link to Santa Cruz parking map is available upon request. We're only a phone call away to answer any of your getting-around questions or to give directions. The Santa Cruz Information booth on Pacific Ave. is very informative and helpful as well.
host_about:
Hello, we're Rex and Briana Solway! We have both lived in Santa Cruz our entire lives, and know the town like the back of our hand(s). We enjoy traveling, fine dining, photography, and the ocean-- we wouldn't be able to live far from the beach! We're avid sushi lovers, die hard Survivor fans, adore cats (but no worries if you have allergies, no kitties live here!), and often find ourselves critiquing the films and shows we watch. We worship the sun, but thrive under the moon and the stars when it's dark outside. We're always looking for the next adventure that awaits around the corner. 

We're dedicated to providing the best possible experience for you and your family, and will create a unique experience you'll never forget!

space: 136 Younger Way is located atop Santa Cruz's Beach Hill, an easy downhill stroll to the Pacific Ocean, Main Beach volleyball courts, the historic Santa Cruz Wharf and the famous Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk. Surfers and boogie boarders are just minutes away from Cowell’s (beginner waves) and Steamer Lane (expert waves). Explore downtown shops, restaurants and coffee shops which are easily accessible by a 10 minute walk. There are endless other recreational options in Santa Cruz County including mountain biking, hiking, sailing, kayaking and scenic trains through redwood forests. host_about:
We moved to Santa Cruz in July 2011 from Chicago.  It's been quite a culture shift; but we love it, we love the relaxed and friendly culture of Santa Cruz, we really think there's no place like it and we have traveled all over the world.   We've traveled to 42 countries together and have a passion for social justice issues; both globally and locally.  Chad recently founded ruly, a social impact company focused on job creation for women in developing economies.  Jodi works as a psychotherapist at UCSC's Counseling & Psychological Services.  Our boys (ages 8 and 9) love living in Santa Cruz; boogie boarding at Cowell's, [playing soccer at Depot Park, or mountain biking at Wilder Ranch.

This listing is for our Primary Residence, which we rent when we travel throughout the year.  Grandparents and extended family are in Michigan, so we spend a lot of time traveling away from Santa Cruz to visit family or to visit more places around the globe!

neighborhood_overview: "The small community of Pleasure Point is a classic beachside community with plenty of local shopping and dining options, home to wetsuit pioneer Jack O'Neill, where locals mix effortlessly with visitors eager to capture that authentic surf vibe. Surfing aficionados can hang loose at Pleasure Point Park, complete with beach access where longtime wave riders compare stories from the day's outings. Pleasure Point boasts surfing events perfect for spectators and nearly a dozen famous breaks making it the ideal destination for skilled surfers and a perfect addition to a Santa Cruz beach vacation."
notes: I offer executive coaching focused on personal or professional success at a special rate for my guests -- 125 per session (cash or charge). More information about coaching can be found on my website, which I will share privately at your request. If you want to reserve the second bedroom, please book for 3 people (even if only 2 are coming).
transit: Walk or bike to many things, including East Cliff, a small convenience store, the beach, Capitola, the Crow's Nest and Twin Lakes, and excellent BBQ. Downtown Santa Cruz is easily accessible. Two blocks from the bus which goes throughout Santa Cruz county.
host_about: Artist, musician, and executive coach enjoying life in a beautiful location.

summary: Come relax and stay right in the heart of delightful lower Seabright in Santa Cruz! A large, unique, colorful, sunny loft with en suite bathroom and big, private deck in a three bedroom home. We are just blocks from Seabright Beach and right around the corner from the Seabright Brewery and other neighborhood fun!
space: The experience is uniquely Santa Cruz in the sought-after lower Seabright neighborhood:  - Exciting, upbeat, bright beachy decor in this fun space sleeps two - Large, light filled, open loft with high ceilings and two sky lights - Private bathroom - Big, private deck with hammock - Super comfortable California king platform bed to ensure the sweetest of sleeps - There is a mini refrigerator in the loft for use during your stay - Vivid colors, clean, high-thread, cotton bedding - No television for a more relaxing stay - Wireless internet - There is a hair dryer in the bathroom for your use  - Access room via a wooden, spiral staircase - House is shared with two amazing and fun downstairs housemates - Non-smoking adults only, please and thank you!

neighborhood_overview: Seabright is our favorite neighborhood in Santa Cruz! Everything you'll need is within walking distance -- the beach, great restaurants, a brewery, a corner store and a couple fun locals bars!  Just a couple short blocks to Seabright Beach and a couple more to the Harbor! Watch the weekly boat races in the summer or go play in the waves, see amazing sea life or catch a stunning sunset just down the street at Seabright Beach! We are also very close to the the Crow's Nest, a popular Santa Cruz harbor beach destination.  You can walk to the Boardwalk in about five minutes as well! The free Friday night beach concerts in the summer are super fun! Not to mention the Boardwalk's rides, games and fun shops.  If you want a bit of a change of pace, you can also walk, ride your bike, drive or catch a cab to downtown. We are located in a banana belt -- we get more sun than our neighboring communities which is perfect for vacationing by the beach!
notes: - There are two housemates in the home who may be there during your stay and I will inform them of your arrival and departure. - The room is open and above the living room and the kitchen. Even though we are a relatively quite home most of the time, my housemates still listen to music, cook and do their thing at different times of day or night. It's usually fairly quiet but not for the super-sensitive quiet-needing person.  - We live behind a brewery so at times during the week it may be a bit loud for short spurts of time (on garbage/recycling days mid-week, for example). - I will send further instructions on what to do upon leaving, etc.  Thank you!
transit: Walking, riding bikes or skateboarding is the preferred mode of transportation in our neighborhood but the Santa Cruz Metro bus line is also conveniently located. It is easy to drive around and in and out of the neighborhood, too!
host_about: Santa Cruz local for over 20 years and proud of it. I currently live in San Francisco (and love it there, too) but I do go back and forth between the two places frequently! The best of both worlds :)

host_about:
My husband and I moved to Santa Cruz 1 1/2 years ago when we bought our early 1900's Craftsman home.  We have had fun renovating our home and the cottage and are looking forward to sharing it with others. We are easy going and enjoy gardening, playing the ukelele and singing on Saturdays down at the Crows Nest beach, and riding our bikes around Santa Cruz. We also like bringing people together to share a meal or just fun times. 

We invite couples and families to stay in our cottage studio and will do our best to help you enjoy a fun stay in this charming city.  We live in Central Park, a tiny neighborhood tucked just off Ocean Street and is walking distance to great restaurants, spas, movie theaters, book stores, Wednesday Farmers Market and fun street musicians.  

We enjoy helping others have a great vacation here in Santa Cruz and can help you coordinate plans and reservations during your stay. 

Things we can't live without: Marianne's Ice Cream, Penny Ice Creamery, Ukelele Club on the beach, black and white cats and each other! And we'll tell you where to get the BEST root beer float in the world! 

Our life motto is
 "Be Always Just as Sweet as This"
and 
 "You can change the world by making a difference to the person right in front of you"

name: Riverside Ranch: Lil Loafer
summary: Tucked amongst the mini-orchard of Riverside Ranch, sits the Lil Loafer; the perfect spot for the solo traveler. Her clean, cream interior invites you to fold your clothes in the cabinet, put your books on the shelf and snuggle down in the twin bed
space: The Lil Loafer is a 1940's vintage trailer settled in among the fruit trees and dwellings of Riverside Ranch. We are a community of artists, writers, activists teachers and kids. This is a quiet and peaceful oasis close to all the amenities Santa Cruz has to offer.  Once you've settled in, step out onto the porch or enjoy snacks or take out in the communal courtyard. Without a kitchen, this little bungalow is the perfect spot for the overnight traveler or someone who enjoys tasting the flavors of the town they visit versus making meals at home. Bring a robe or comfy lounge wear to make the walk across the courtyard to the shared bathroom (shared with the studio) and enjoy a soak or a shower in the claw foot bathtub. A water dispenser with fresh water and drinking glass are provided to keep you refreshed, please let us know if you need additional glasses.  The lot is shared with another rental stucco (The Moon) as well as a permanent dwellers in the front stucco  and three-bedroom house

neighborhood_overview: This wonderful, convenient location is on a quiet residential street just a few minutes walk from downtown, the Boardwalk, and Main Beach. You can hear the sound of the waves when the wind blows just right.
transit: Walking and biking is how we think it is best, but you can easily take a 10 minute walk to the bus station downtown or bus stops mere blocks away. If you are driving, there is first come, first serve parking in the driveway (room for 3 cars) and street parking.
host_about:
Hello, my name is Charlotte and I am excited to be a host for Airbnb. I love meeting new people and look forward to hosting folks coming through town. I live right next door to this rental with my adorable Jack Russell, Jerry Lee, so I will be available and nearby if you have any questions. 

I am a textile artist and own my own small business called Stand West, where I design and hand make a range of luxury, eco conscious accessories using custom dyed fabrics and mostly repurposed materials. If you are extra curious check out @standwestcreations on Instagram. 

In addition to Stand West I am a Hip Hop Dance Teacher and work with Crush Sunglasses (a company based in the LA area) as their Northern California lifestyle rep. 

Despite growing up in beautiful Colorado and having the opportunity to explore every state in the USA, Santa Cruz has a strong hold on my heart. Here I spend the majority of my free time at the skate park located just a few blocks from Riverside Ranch, running on West Cliff, visiting the farmers markets that are held every day of the week throughout town, taking my dog to the beach, hiking in the redwoods with friends, and working with the community to make this city even better then it already is. 

I have been blessed beyond my own imagination to travel many places across the globe through the benefits of having  a mother as a Airline Stewardess. Because of all of my experiences being away from home I have a huge heart for making sure that your stay is the best it can be. Staying somewhere that feels like home, rather then in a hotel, makes all of the difference for me when I am exploring new places. Thank God for Airbnb. ; ) 

I hope to have the chance to get to know you and whether or not you decide to stay at Riverside Ranch I'll be wishing for you the best experiences while you are here in Santa Cruz. 

Light and Love!

Charlie

neighborhood_overview: The house is a 3 minute walk to the beach. A 2 minute walk to the Yacht Harbor (or less!) and a 3 minute walk to the Crow's Nest (restaurant, bar, great outdoor dining), Palomar (mexican bar & restaurant), Kind Grind (coffee), and Johnnys (great seafood restaurant). Aldo's restaurant is a fun, free boat ride across to the other side of the harbor. Probably takes 5 mins. We are about a 15-20 min stroll to the Beach Boardwalk over some lovely sea walls and bridges. It takes about 10 mins (1 mile) to get to the Seabright Brewery and restaurants on Seabright Ave. There is a pizza place, Italian pasta place, and adorable cafe over there on Seabright. The house is also a 4 min walk (or less) to Harbor Cafe which is a great place for brunch and mimosas.
host_about:
I purchased Casa de Alta Loma in 2013 as the fulfillment of a life-long dream to live close to a beautiful beach, in an environment that soothes the soul. I have lived in and around Santa Cruz for a decade now and finally decided on just the right spot (Live Oaks) and the perfect home (Alta Loma). I use it often and enjoy the environment tremendously.  For example, Stand Up Paddle in the harbor and out to sea is one of my favorite things to do - The SUP shack is minutes from my doorstep and if you're lucky, you'll see all sorts of marine life (whales too!). It's such a unique place - we even have a Saturday morning Ukelele sing-along down on the beach.  We usually get coffee at the Kind Grind (right there on the beach) and just listen.  My 4 yr. old niece has even played along with the crowd.  (Don't expect skilled musicians but do expect friendliness and old time sing-along songs.) We have a Live Oak Farmer's Market on Sunday which is fantastic too!

I love to entertain my friends and family from the East Coast at the beach house - they just cannot get over how idyllic life in Santa Cruz can be. I was born and raised outside of Boston, MA and relocated to the West Coast to work in the Software Industry. I hope you come enjoy Casa de Alta Loma and all it has to offer.
The location is ideal. You can hear the ocean, the sea lions, and the gulls but not the young neighboring renters who are right down on the beach.  It's a 2 minute walk to the harbor where you will find a favorite restaurant -- Johnny's Harborside.  It's a 4 minute walk to the beach which is wide and long. I often run the entire stretch from my beach down to the Santa Cruz Boardwalk all on the sand (at low tide!). It's about 13 minutes walk to the east entrance of the famous Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk.
Driving gets you to a lot of popular destinations: E.g., Shadowbrook restaurant in Capitola is 3 miles away and SF and Big Sur are each about an hour and a half away, in opposite directions.

neighborhood_overview: We live in my favorite neighborhood in Santa Cruz! We are just walking minutes from the beach, and the harbor, cute restaurants coffee shops, and even a climbing gym! We are in one of the oldest neighborhoods in Santa Cruz, and just walking around and looking at all of the cute colorful Beach Cottages is like going back in time. Most of these homes including our own wer build at the turn of the 20th century, some even before, so it's quite a treat to be around all of this beauty and history just minutes from the ocean. Some great places to eat near by: The Seabright Brewery, The Seabreeze Cafe, Java Junction, the Crepe Place, the Crow's Nest, Betty's Burgers, La Posta, Engfer Pizza Works, Lilian's, Charlie Hong-Kong's, The Bagelry, Thai House, Laili, Harbor Cafe, Tramonti, The Harbor Cafe, Cafe Brazil, and many more to choose from. We are also in close proximity to the best Natural Food stores in town, Staff of Life, Shopper's Corner, and Whole Foods.  And if you feel like renting a bi
notes: You will truly love staying in the perfect neighborhood in Santa Cruz, where you are close enough to the beach that you can hear the waves crashing at night, but far enough away that the barking of the sea-lions won't get on your nerves ;) Our home is old, so please excuse the exterior appearance as we are awaiting a new paint job, and the plants in front are kind of drab at the moment.
transit: Walking is great, bike riding, and buses are all really accessible. You can walk to a great coffee shop in 5 minutes, and to numerous restaurants, or hop on the bus to another part of town on Seabright Ave, or Soquel Ave. There are bike shops close by where you could rent bikes if needed for an adventure.
host_about: I am a Dancer, Fashion Designer, Artist, that was living in Salvador Brazil for the last 4 years, and just moved back to Santa Cruz, after 10 years of wandering around. In Brazil I spend most of my time in dance classes, rehearsals, workshops, performing, out at dance performances, music events, surfing, or at home designing clothing in my studio. I met my husband Cristiano there, and he moved to California with me to experience life here.  We acquired this house, which is a definite fixer-upper, but we have made our way through a lot of projects one after another. We are still awaiting a great paint job, and some yard work, but the inside of our house by far surpasses it's outer appeal, lol. We are very accommodating to our guests, and are very centrally located close to everything! We also did Airbnb in Brazil when we were living there for about 2 years, and had a number of international guests stay with us. As you will see all of the reviews we got from our prior listings. We love Airbnb! It's a great way to rent out your space, and make friends while you are at it! :) I hope that you will enjoy our place here in the beautiful Santa Cruz!!! FYI I also teach private surf lessons and provide a surf board if you are interested...

Guests can use the kitchen, which is fully furnished and the back patio, which is filled with vegetables, herbs, and flowers - a perfect place to enjoy a cup of coffee. A private parking space is available right out front.

host_about:
Well, I am in my 30's and married to my wonderful husband, Daniel for the past 6 years.  Our children include our amazing dog and our beautiful horse that mean the world to us.  By day, I work in the veterinary field and my husband teaches environmental science to kids.  During our free time, together we enjoy traveling, snow boarding, rock climbing, scuba diving, music festivals and camping.  My biggest passion is horseback riding and my husband is a die hard surfer who also enjoys working in the garden and relaxing in his hammock while listening to reggae tunes.  We are both very passionate about the environment and doing our part to reduce our footprint on this planet. 
 We love traveling and seeing the world and we make an effort to travel out of the county about every other year.  We have been to places such as Indonesia, Thailand, Malaysia, Costa Rica, Panama, Nicaragua, Hawaii, Europe, Philippines and Sri Lanka.   When we travel, we travel without any specific agenda and let life guide us to where we belong.  All we need is our trusty Lonely Planet guide book and we find ourselves at great hostels where like minded travelers gather to share stories and experiences.  We enjoy good company and fun positive people that inspire us to become better individuals.  We are fortunate in where we live and the beautiful home we live in and we would be blessed to share it with others while we are out on our own life adventures.  Our motto in life: "Find what you love and love what you find."

neighborhood_overview: Leisurely walk to Black's, Twin Lakes, and Sunny Cove beaches. Great groceries, farmers market, cafes, and restaurants within walking distance. Easy bike ride to Pleasure Point surfing (1 mile west), Capitola (2 miles east), and downtown (3 miles west). notes: The Transient Occupancy tax for AirB&B rooms in Santa Cruz county is 11%.  We ask that you pay us in the folder you will see on the desk when you arrive, either with a personal check or cash.
transit: Bike travel is a dream with bike lanes all through town, and longer bike trails in the area. You can easily rent bikes nearby, or borrow ours. When we are home we travel almost exclusively by bike.  Our location is very convenient for public transportation.  The bus stop is around the corner that takes you directly to downtown Santa Cruz. The local bus service hooks up with service to San Jose, Caltrain, and all the Bay Area Transit systems including both San Jose and San Francisco Airports. From the airport, use Bay Area Transit system to Diridon Station in San Jose. From there you can catch the Hwy 17 Express to Santa Cruz. From the Santa Cruz downtown station take Santa Cruz Metro Bus 66 or 68 (Live Oak) to the bus stop nearest the intersection of 17th and Portola. The intersection is 2 blocks from our house.  Car travel is convenient. We are the last exit before HWY 1 merges to two lanes so we rarely fight traffic. Street parking with no meters along our street. We use our carport

You have your own private entrance with easy access and off street parking behind the apartment. You have full access to the wrap around deck and large courtyard in the back of the apartment.  We'll provide additional instructions including a unique four digit code
neighborhood_overview: This is the perfect space for two people to enjoy the downtown charm of Santa Cruz. A pull out bed in the living room provides an additional full bed for one or two guests. Use it as a launching point to explore downtown restaurants and the boardwalk or for a surf weekend with its close proximity to the beach or visit your student at the UCSC. The house is nestled within Santa Cruz's historic Victorians. This is a true Santa Cruz neighborhood with convenient access to the best the city has to offer. It's a very quiet neighborhood.
transit: The Mission Santa Cruz and downtown Pacific Mall are an easy 5 minute walk away as are many of Santa Cruz's finest restaurants. A 20 minute walk will take you to the Santa Cruz Wharf, Beach Boardwalk, and public beaches. A few more minutes and you'll be walking or biking on West Cliff where you'll see some of the finest surfing around. For those with a car, UCSC is a short drive away. Hike among the redwoods at Pogonip or the hills of Wilder Ranch. The location is also bike friendly with easy access to the river levee where a short ride brings you to the wharf, boardwalk and West Cliff. A little further and you'll find some of the finest mountain biking around.
host_about: We're Michael and Mary Kaye. We're active hikers, bikers and surfers and love meeting new people. We love to walk downtown to hear local music and see the latest movies after enjoying one of our many restaurants. We respect your privacy and your private entrance will allow you to seek us out if you want to learn a little more about the area or want to borrow a bike or surfboard.

summary: Centrally located above the Harbor, this luxurious beach rancheria is an incredible vacation home.  Included with: 3 bedrooms, a massive living room, posh dining room, fully equipped kitchen, full bathroom, and giant backyard lounge with outdoor tub!
space: This adorable beach cottage is the perfect vacation rental for summer getaways! Tons of sun and patio space outdoors. **The Best Santa Cruz Beach Deal on AirBnb!**  Spacious and Luxurious 3 bedroom stand-alone house has a kitchen, full bathroom, living room, dining room, and 2 bedrooms/1 office room. Located in the quiet,sunny, and quaint neighborhood near the Harbor, Arrana Gulch, and Twin Lakes beaches- this is ideal for a clean, responsible, and respectable couple, family, or friends. We also have one resident kitty who is very sweet and independent. Just letting her in and out, feeding, and watering her are the only requirements for cat-care! neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is the ultimate vacationer's dream!  We are centrally located to everything you might want to visit while your here, but out of the mania that the downtown Santa Cruz area can bring during the summer season.  We are a walk to the Santa Cruz Harbor where there is sailing, stand up paddle boarding, whale watching, and several restaurants.  Very close to our house at the end of our street there is beautiful Jose Avenue Park with a skate park, basketball courts, playground, and horseshoe pits.  We are within walking distance to Coffeetopia coffee shop, El Jardin Mexican Cuisine, Live Oak Market & Liquors.  If you do not want to drive while you're visiting, this is a great spot to be in.  Guests in the past have even hopped on the local bus line (which picks up at the end of our street) for the 2 minute ride to the Live Oak Beaches!
notes: We do have a sweet independent resident cat name Kona who would need love, food, and water while you're visiting
transit: We are right near a public bus pick up which is about 2 minutes from the Capitola Mall and numerous Live Oak Beaches.  Our local Santa Cruz Bus lines are cheap, convenient, and go to all the summer hot spots.  Cabs/Taxis are also cheap (about 5 from our house to downtown Pacific Ave.)  We also have a 2 car driveway, so if you have a rental car you will not have to park it on the street.  Bike riding is our method of transportation we prefer.  There is a bike rental shop right around the corner from our house!
host_about: I am a young professional who loves the outdoors and traveling.  I work as a Naturalist at an outdoor science school that specializes in 5th grade science curriculum.  I enjoy hiking, cooking, playing music, taking bike rides, camping, backpacking, and adventuring.  In the summer when I'm not teaching, I leave my house in Santa Cruz to take backpacking/camping trips in the Sierras and Trinity Alps.  I like to have tons of fun but also keep a tidy household.

space: Everything here has been upgraded for your  convenience and comfort.   The queen-sized bed includes cotton bedding and extra pillows and blankets. There is an armoire to hang and store clothes, shoes, etc.  The setee expands to lounge or sleep.  There is a flat screen HDTV equipped with DirectTV and streaming Netflix through DVD player.   The small kitchen is well equipped and has filtered water, an espresso machine, coffee maker/grinder and waffle maker. Dishes, glasses, utensils, linens and cleaning supplies are provided. Iron, ironing board and hair dryer if you need them.

neighborhood_overview: The studio is in a beachy, residential neighborhood 1.3 miles from Pleasure Point and 1.3 miles from the Capitola beach.  You can easily walk several blocks to Trader Joe's, Target, Whole Foods and other local shops and cafes.
notes: You may see a small white cat sometimes.  Her name is Billie and she lives with me in the front but is an indoor/outdoor cat.
transit: Santa Cruz has much to offer. Walk on the many beaches, have fun at the world famous boardwalk, watch world class surfing, check out wineries, explore the redwoods  and visit the beautiful UCSC campus. Downtown Santa Cruz and Capitola have lots of restaurants and stores. There is also a lively arts community and lots of opportunities to hear live music and other performances. A Metro bus stop is within a couple of blocks that takes you downtown and other destinations.  The drive to San Francisco takes 1 1/2 hours  and to Carmel, Pacific Grove and Monterey, about an hour.   If you are arriving by plane, San Jose Airport is a 45 minute drive  and San Francisco Int'l is 1 hour and 15 minutes away.

neighborhood_overview: I live in an area that is made up of cul de sacs. Most of the homes are 2 story houses that are well maintained. Many of the neighbors have lived here for over 30 years and that gives the neighborhood a feeling of stability. It is generally quiet; however, i do have new neighbors who have loud gatherings on occasion.  There have been a few times I have had to ask them to quiet down as the night goes on. There is plenty of free street parking.  It is great to be within walking distance of major shopping (trader joe's) and the 2 different great beaches.
notes: We are centrally located right off of the 41st ave exit of highway 1.  We are 2 miles from capitola village and pleasure point.   I have a state park pass .  If you are staying for a week, the long term price of 550 will include up to 3 extra people at no charge!
transit: the bus stop is about 4 blocks away.  the bus station at the capitola mall is a five minute walk away.  You can walk to the beach(15 minutes) or shopping and restaurants.
host_about:

I love the beach and the redwoods.  I know lots of wonderful hiking trails, beaches and river spots. my family and I love to travel  and just went on a cross country train trip. we love to see new places and meet new people!
I want my guests to be comfortable.  i am flexible and accommodating.  
if you like dogs and want to meet my great dane Maisy, no problem!  i would love to show off my garden, too.  just ask!

notes: We have an independent indoor/outdoor cat. You do not have to care for him (a neighbor will feed him and he's mostly outside anyway), but he is likely to get inside during your stay. name: Heavenly Ocean View Room w/Queen
summary: This room offers unobstructed views across Santa Cruz and the Monterey Bay.  South facing, this large room gets lots of light. Features 10' coved ceilings, antiques, closet with mini-fridge, blackout curtains, fir floors. Lots of heart & soul!
space: The Dake House as it is known in the Santa Cruz Historic Registry, was built in 1904 by Clarence Dake with the generous support of his wife’s family money. He was a gentleman farmer and started the first escrow/title business in Santa Cruz. The house sits on a hill overlooking the town of Santa Cruz, the mission and the sweeping views of the Monterey Bay and the Boardwalk. While High Street is centrally located of the main routes to UCSC, most of the 2/3 acre property is surrounded by nature. Red tail hawks soar and perch in the tall trees, deer regularly come by to graze, and the hummingbirds love all the salvias in the garden.  The ‘Heavenly View Room” is large room with a firm,  comfortable queen bed on brass bed frame.  Located on the second floor, on south side of the house, the room has 10’ coved ceilings, antique lighting, antique desk and dresser, a mini refrigerator in the closet, and a chair. The nearby shared bathroom has a shower, toilet and sink.   This is one bedroom in a

neighborhood_overview: The location is easily accessible from Mission Street/Highway 1, on the #10 bus line (to and from the nearby UCSC), a few minutes drive (or 10 minute walk) to downtown, hiking trails of the Pogonip, the arboretum, and near all the attractions of the Santa Cruz beach, West Cliff and boardwalk.
transit: Airport-We are about 40 minutes to San Jose International Airport (SJC). San Francisco Airport (SFO) is about 1 hour and 30 minutes without traffic. Los Angeles Airport (LAX) is about a 6 hour drive to the south using the fastest routes.  Train-Amtrak train is about 30 minutes away (in Salinas). You can take a connector bus from downtown Santa Cruz metro station.  Walking to Downtown: Go downhill (East) on High Street. Cross over Highway 1 bridge. Continue on High Street. Cross park diagonally. Cross at crosswalk and walk down hill on Water Street. The Clock Tower and Pacific Avenue are at the bottom of the hill. Downtown will be to your right.  Other walking destinations: it is about a 20 minute uphill walk through a residential neighborhood to get to the hiking trails of the Pogonip. I recommend going down High Street to Highland. Make a left and walk up Highland to Spring Street. Pogonip trails are at the end of Spring Street.  Bus #10 High Street bus will take you to UCSC. (nearest

Dear Guests,   Welcome to Santa Cruz!

neighborhood_overview: You will love the convenience of being able to walk downtown or ride our bikes to the beach! Downtown Santa Cruz is the best place to stay in my opinion. It is full of color and flavor and very beachy bohemian. There are lots of organic local made and inexpensive options for food as well as great cafes and lots of local made designers. Youll love shopping downtown as it is unique but inexpensive. Seabright is the closest beach and it is one of the best. The lighthouse is there and you will usually see otters swimming along the shore like mermaids. You can also go around the rocky cliff to the beach boardwalk. Sunsets are gorgeous. There is also a marsh downtown that is really nice to walk around if the beach is crowded. If you are here on the first friday of the month, this is called "First Friday" in Santa cruz and starting about 5pm the entire downtown will be filled with happy people walking around at art galleries and also take a quick hop over to the Tannery which also celebrates
notes: This is my home and a little 5lb pomeranian lives here with me. If you have a well behaved little dog and we discuss it ahead of time it would be ok, but no dogs over 15lbs. The house is professionally cleaned before you arrive.
transit: Street parking is usually available on the street right in front of the main house although now that it is the high season it may sometimes be necessary to look on an adjacent street to find parking. We are just two blocks from the downtown Santa Cruz transit center where you can find buses anywhere in the region. You can ride our 2 bikes downtown but be sure to lock them up well as bike theft is high in Santa Cruz. There is also a local trolley that can take you frm downtown to the beach.

host_about:
I am a 48 years young woman.  I live by myself, though I have good friends and a wonderful boyfriend.
I have been a musician and a stained glass artist for decades, but recently I developed a new profession, I am a lymphedema therapist.  I treat clients/patients in my own house, so I live my home fully.
I love to garden, to grow what I eat, to go out with my bicycle..when there's time!!  Beautiful walks by the ocean around here. I love to see live music in small venues, and Santa Cruz is great for that.
I travel a lot,  I go to Italy every year, since that's where I am from.  My entire family is there...but when I can, I go for long trips in other continents, other worlds, and find out how people live their lives in different corners of the world.
I like to cook for friends, so my kitchen has every thing one might need, and I set up my home so that I can have friends visiting, spending time in the garden, spending the night...  hurray for friends!

Since I want comfort and convenience when I travel I try to make that possible for my guests.

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood has sidewalks and a really great health food store, The Food Bin, is around the corner.  The best breakfast place in town, Cafe Brazil, is around the corner as well.
notes: Our home is not one of those model homes, it is well loved and lived in. We like to travel with our resources rather than perfect our space. Some things need paint, etc. but it is cozy, clean, and fabulous.  All sheets & Towels included.  We ask for a 80. cleaning fee to keep it clean and fabulous. The city of Santa Cruz Charges an 11% Tax for Airbnb-- many hosts charge this to their guests upon arrival, on top of their prices, ours is included! Nearby Farmers Markets are Wednesdays downtown and Saturdays on the Westside. There is often music and tables and chairs set out on Saturday.  Ride your bike to breakfast at the market & continue on the bike trails along the coast.
transit: Public transport runs on nearby Mission street both north and south. One of our favorite day adventures is taking the bus out to Davenport and walking along the coast along the railroad tracks and farm land back to our house. Its about 11 miles, between 3 1/2 and 4 hours.  Even better you can rent bikes for 6.00 per hour around the corner and tour the beach, the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk, and many single track and other mountain biking trails north along the coast.

space: We are right in the middle of everything! You can drive to most destinations in the city within 5-10 mins this includes beaches, the boardwalk, downtown, UCSC, Cabrillo and so much more!

We both grew up in Santa Cruz and are very familiar with good places to eat and drink and some of the lesser known gems in Santa Cruz! We're friendly, don't be afraid to reach out if you have questions! We also love getting feedback on the place! Please let us know if there's something we can do to improve your stay! Our number one concern is that you enjoy your stay as much as possible! The house is located in the Branciforte neighborho
neighborhood_overview: The house is located in the Branciforte neighborhood of the banana belt! This is one of the oldest and nicest neighborhoods in Santa Cruz.  DeLaveaga golf course and disc golf course are a block or so away.  There is mountain biking, hiking and a dog park all within a block of the house.  A 2 minute drive gets you to stores satisfying any essentials you may need including Whole Foods, Rite Aid and excellent local dining.  Head a few blocks more and you will end up downtown or at the Beach Boardwalk! Locals love the neighborhood due to its central location and the ability to avoid a lot of the summer traffic congestion.
transit: Its a short drive to nearly anything in Santa Cruz and there is ample parking in the driveway and on the street!
host_about:
We are both Santa Cruz natives, born and raised. We both love our town and are excited to share it with you! 

We are happily married and live with our wonderful 10 year old daughter. We LOVE to travel (our most recent trips include Portugal, Spain, and Peru)! We LOVE food (cooking, eating, trying new foods, you name it!) We love to be outdoors. We love to go backpacking, go for hikes, ride our bikes, and mushroom forage (no wonder we love Santa Cruz so much...). Most of all, we love to spend time with our friends and family. 

This was our very first house that we bought almost 4 years ago. To say it was a fixer-upper is an understatement! We did as much of the work ourselves as we could manage. We are really proud of the way it turned out! We are thoroughly enjoying sharing our house and our home town with others on Airbnb! Our guests satisfaction is our number one priority and we are constantly striving to be better!

neighborhood_overview: Quiet, peaceful, seaside home-owner neighborhood.  (And if you open the windows you may well hear barking seals and surf when it’s raging.)
notes: In the Aloha spirit, one half of the net revenue we receive from Airbnb is donated through the Community Foundation of Santa Cruz County to support people in need and worthy causes. The City of Santa Cruz levies an 11% Transient Occupancy Tax to be paid by all short-term guests.  Even though most cities have such a “hotel tax,” Airbnb isn’t yet set up to charge this (hopefully that changes soon!), and hosts are not allowed to include it in the rates.  Therefore we need to ask you to bring with you a check (payable to the City of Santa Cruz) or cash equivalent to 11% of what you paid airbnb.  Apologies for the awkwardness of this, and thank you for your understanding.
transit: Free on-street parking.  You will be about a half hour from San Jose Airport and Silicon Valley and a little over an hour from San Francisco/SFO.  45 minutes to Carmel and Monterey with its world-famous Aquarium on Cannery Row – and not far beyond that is Big Sur. There are numerous California state parks within 10 minutes to an hour’s drive.

space: No Cleaning Fee. Weekly lodging in a restored 1888 grand victorian treasure in downtown Santa Cruz. The perfect location for walking, dining, shopping, and people-(website hidden) gives us a rating of "Walker's Paradise" with 100 out of 100 points for walkability.  There are 5 rooms on the third floor of the Hinds House to choose from. These rooms all have bathrooms across the hall.  We also have higher priced rooms on the second floor with private bathrooms. host_about:
Hello There! 

I am a bay area native with a penchant for traveling far and wide. I try to travel as much as possible and also lived in Italy for 5 years. I love wining, dining and dancing! 
When I travel, I like to get into the vibe of a city as a local would do and always try to rent an apartment over a hotel as living in a neighborhood, having a kitchen, and catching a glimpse of what it would be like to live in the city I am visiting, adds to the experience of travel and make it more authentic and less touristy. I love to walk everywhere whenever possible so love to visit and explore cities that are walkable.. shopping and sightseeing by day and eating, drinking and dancing by night. I used to help students traveling abroad to Italy by finding them apartments, planning adventures for them and recommending all my favorite spots! I love to share my recommendations with people as having an amazing meal, or visiting a site that is not in a guidebook always make for a memorable trip. 

Life is short, live it to the fullest!

neighborhood_overview: Our spacious downtown vacation home is great for any occasion-- whether you want to spend a few days at the beach with your family, go hiking in the beautiful redwood forests our town has to offer, ride the Giant Dipper and enjoy a funnel cake at the Boardwalk, see the monarch butterflies nest at Natural Bridges State Park, have the perfect weekend getaway with your special someone, get a seafood dinner with an ocean view on the wharf, take a stroll down the beautiful backdrop of West Cliff Dr., or would just like enjoy some peace and quiet in a serene environment-- you've come to the right place! Walk to the farmers market  on Wednesdays and make yourself a gourmet meal in the large fully equipped kitchen. Everything we mentioned is in walking distance, you wouldn't even need to rent a car! The home is located in the heart of downtown Santa Cruz, but you wouldn't even know it! So peaceful and serene, it is extremely quiet, so much so, if you listen hard enough you can sometimes hear t
notes: ********************** Check in is at 4PM ********************** Check out is at 11AM ********************** For guests that are planning on going to The Boardwalk:  Consider staying with us on a Monday or a Tuesday, as the Boardwalk has 1.00 rides, hot dogs, cotton candy & soda from 5PM to closing. It's a great bargain and tons of fun!  In accordance to Santa Cruz city laws, there will be a separate 11% transit occupancy tax to be paid in cash or check upon check in please. Based on availability, we offer an airport pickup and drop-off from SJO or SFO for an extra fee. Please let us know in advance if this is something you're interested in.  The house is equipped with basic spices, oils, salt/pepper, etc. in the kitchen. We have lots of extra towels, blankets and pillows.  YOU WILL NOT BE CHARGED FOR THE DEPOSIT. It is only an agreement that if you were to damage the house (spill wine on the carpet, break a window, etc) you agree to be financially responsible.  We strive to make stay
transit: Walking and biking is the best way to appreciate the Santa Cruz scenery.  However, car rental services are available. There is a bus station on Pacific Ave. but there are many bus stops closer to your home away from home. The Metro Bus Station is where both local buses and Greyhound buses depart from. The Santa Cruz Trolley loops around Pacific Ave. and goes to the wharf and Boardwalk for only 25 cents! You can rent segway scooters down the street from the Boardwalk to use in that area. Information regarding rental services will be included in our information pamphlet, or emailed upon request. We do have a single parking driveway, and allot 2 guest passes for the permitted street parking.  We're only a phone call away to answer any of your getting-around questions or to give directions. The Santa Cruz Information booth on Pacific Ave. is very informative and helpful as well.
host_about:
Hello, we're Rex and Briana Solway! We have both lived in Santa Cruz our entire lives, and know the town like the back of our hand(s). We enjoy traveling, fine dining, photography, and the ocean-- we wouldn't be able to live far from the beach! We're avid sushi lovers, die hard Survivor fans, adore cats (but no worries if you have allergies, no kitties live here!), and often find ourselves critiquing the films and shows we watch. We worship the sun, but thrive under the moon and the stars when it's dark outside. We're always looking for the next adventure that awaits around the corner. 

We're dedicated to providing the best possible experience for you and your family, and will create a unique experience you'll never forget!

neighborhood_overview: We love being so close to downtown and being able to ride bikes and walk everywhere! There will be some suggested activities including where to rent bikes and get surfing lessons when you arrive. The neighborhood is a very eclectic mix. Many single, 30 something professionals, young Latino families, college kids, hipsters, travelers, and artists. We love the hip, young, colorful vibe.
notes: My partner (Leah) and I recently bought this home and have plans for a remodel as we turn it into our dream home. While we await building permits we figured renting it over the summer would be a great way to help us with some of the building costs and bring some good juju to the house with fantastic people who will love visiting Santa Cruz. We welcome all the laughs, peace, and fun you likely will enjoy while visiting the property. May it bless you the way it is blessing us. BEWARE > Santa Cruz is known for petty theft... no matter where you stay... lock up the cars and gates to keep bikes safe.
transit: With so much to do within walking distance including grocery shopping and the beach... you really don't need a car. However there's plenty of street parking and most of downtown is metered parking. Our neighborhood is perfect for biking, bring your own or rent one from one of the bike shops nearby. The bus system around Santa Cruz is relatively good. There's a bus stop on our street. Taxi's are readily available and Uber is here too! We recommend the Santa Cruz Flyer if you need an airport ride.  The closest airport to Santa Cruz is San Jose (35 minutes) - airport code: SJC. Other airports would be Oakland (OAK), San Francisco (SFO), Monterey (MRY)
host_about: Recently retired from the auto collision industry.  Currently loving life, traveling as much as I can, and exploring new things all of the time.  I'm passionate about reading, learning, growing, and being active.  I love beautiful healthy food and I enjoy dining out.

neighborhood_overview: We are blessed to live so close to so many good places to eat, drink and shop for food, as well as within walking or biking distance from really all Santa Cruz has to offer, from mountain biking, hiking, surfing, swimming, kayaking, SUPing, to walking or biking to downtown, or up to UCSC.  We live in  a quiet and safe family neighborhood where it is safe to walk day or night.
notes: The city of Santa Cruz levies an 11% Transient Occupancy Tax that is included in the price, which we then give to the city. Santa Cruz City TOT Registration Certificate #670-955
transit: Public transportation runs regularly just a couple of blocks away.  Visitors are welcome to park in the driveway, or on the street where there is plenty of parking.  There are numerous airport services that will pick you up and drop you off at SFO or San Jose International .
host_about: My wife and I and our 2 kids (now teenagers) love living in Santa Cruz!  Andi and I both work in community health care and love spending out time outdoors staying active:  hiking, mountain biking, or just walking along Westcliff or going to the beach with our dogs.  We also love to stay close to home and work in the yard and garden where we can visit with our chickens and rabbit.  We feel blessed to live in this beautiful area.  Here on the "Westside" we can walk to great eateries, brew pubs, wineries, and go shopping just up the road at the local health food store. We are a busy family with the kids engaged in sports and music, but love to spend time visiting with our guests - sharing a glass of wine or a pint of ale helping you get the lay of the land and work on interesting itineraries. If time and schedules permit maybe we could even get out on the bay in kayaks or stand up paddle boards where you can get up close and personal with otters, seals and whales, or get into the into Santa Cruz's amazing mountains on mountain bikes, then hit up the organic microbrew pub on the way home....  So much to do - all without ever needing to get into your car!

space: The Dake House as it is known in the Santa Cruz Historic Registry, was built in 1904 by Clarence Dake with the generous support of his wife’s family money. He was a gentleman farmer and started the first escrow/title business in Santa Cruz. The house sits on a hill overlooking the town of Santa Cruz, the mission and the sweeping views of the Monterey Bay and the Boardwalk. While High Street is centrally located of the main routes to UCSC, most of the 2/3 acre property is surrounded by nature. Red tail hawks soar and perch in the tall trees, deer regularly come by to graze, and the hummingbirds love all the salvias in the garden.    The ‘Mission View Room’ is a small, cozy room with a firm and comfortable queen bed with iron bed frame.  Located on the northeast side of the house, the room has 10’ coved ceilings, antique lighting, a mini refrigerator in the small closet, a chair, and dresser with mirror. The midtown area is close to the redwoods, beaches, and downtown but has its own charms. We have a mini-mart, 2 natural food stores, and a classic market within a mile.  Check out our bakery and cafes- you won't find better! Farmer's Markets are  in the area 4 days a week. You
neighborhood_overview: The midtown area is close to the redwoods, beaches, and downtown but has its own charms. We have a mini-mart, 2 natural food stores, and a classic market within a mile.  Check out our bakery and cafes- you won't find better! Farmer's Markets are  in the area 4 days a week.
notes: Our house was built a hundred years ago and we have loved our home for 29 years. Now that the kids have launched, we look forward to sharing our gem with you. The city of Santa Cruz charges an 11% tax for AirBnB- we include this in our price rather than adding it upon arrival. Our little dog Heidi stays with us in the front unit- you might hear her yips at times. Let us know if you want to meet her-she is a 4 year old rescue Italian greyhound/terrier mix. Once she knows you, there is NO ONE happier to see you than Heidi when you get home!
transit: You can park in our driveway with super easy access to highways 1 and 17. There is regular bus service one block away to downtown- and transfer to the University- or to points southeast. The Highway 17 bus to San Jose has a stop 5 minutes from here. We are centrally located and an easy bike or walk to downtown, DeLaveaga park, and Seabright Beach. We will give you a map and can suggest fast or scenic routes to your destinations.
host_about:
Lucky to live in a  beautiful place with wonderful people and blessed to be able to wander enough to know there are so many more. Traveling yet getting to "live like a local" is the best! 
I have had an amazing journey as a nurse helping with beginnings at birth and breastfeeding, and now as a caregiver for my husband's voyage through Alzheimer's. We are proud parents of two who have launched and now we are completely owned by our little doggie. 
We are all pilgrims on this camino- Ultreia!

neighborhood_overview: Live Oak is an unincorporated mid county area situated between the cities of Santa Cruz and Capitola extending from Pleasure Point at the coast to the village of Soquel!  Our home is a 5 minute bike ride from the beach and close to the surfing mecca of famed Pleasure Point breaks and the Yacht Harbor. Close by is the upper yacht harbor entrance to the new bike/bridge path across Arana Gulch that is both scenic and fun.  Santa Cruz is a unique and special place that can revive your spirit quickly, especially here on this beautiful Santa Cruz property!
notes: We have a cat . We are dog friendly and expect dog owners arriving with pets to be responsible to our property and respectful of other guest privacy and keep dogs on a leash unless they are in the yard with them. Dog park walking distance from house and dog friendly restaurants on restaurant list.  We must collect a Transient Occupancy Tax for Santa Cruz. To explain the TOT, here is a link to the requirement. (website hidden)_faqs.htm . You can write  a check  and I  we will give you a receipt. Airbnb is soon to collect this themselves as they do in so many other cities
transit: There is a public transit stop two blocks away. Generally parking is available in half of our driveway or safe street parking is close by. With the advent of smart phone GPS a lengthy description on how to get here from nearby airports isn't necessary.
host_about:
Former California Highway Patrolman and grandfather to ten grandchildren including now 4-year-old twins who live in LA. Love the ocean, both in it and on it,gardening, biking,walking in beautiful Santa Cruz, especially along the new E. Cliff Ave walkway. After leaving the highway patrol,  I went from CHiPS to chocolate chips as I am also the former VP of Sales and Marketing for the Pacific Cookie Company here in Santa Cruz.  Author and Founder of DriversYoga (website hidden) a mental technique to keep you in the moment while driving.Most say I get along well with being a very genial host.
You can talk to me about Nowhere Yoga!
We have created a unique garden landscape full of beauty and sound in the mode of a zen temple between the cities of Santa Cruz and Capitola. A visual stress remover! Come and experience, we're here for you. A relaxed self download if you will!
Airbnb ask me to tell guest if I have a life motto. Well yes in fact I do; flexible indecision with all seriousness aside and forward to the rear! It''s always 'the ole same space'
And if you come, welcome to Santa Cruz and Nobody's Inn 
Aloha and Namaste
Pete

neighborhood_overview: You can park your car and not need to drive again for your entire stay! Our street marks the exact halfway point for the famous Wharf to Wharf race.  Blacks Beach is just a 3-minute walk down the street. There are fabulous neighborhood restaurants and coffee shops within walking distance. And a Mexican market is just a block away where you can get the basics. On Sundays, one of Santa Cruz’s unique and bountiful Farmers Markets sets up in the East Cliff Shopping Center, which is short walk from the house. Also within walking / biking distance is Sunny Cove, Pleasure Point, 41st Avenue. In the other direction is the Harbor, which is located at Twin Lakes State Beach. The Crows Nest hosts a Thursday evening summer beach BBQ with live music. Our neighbors are all within close proximity. They appreciate courteous and respectful guests.
transit: There is a Muni bus stop just a short walk from the house. Street parking is available in front of the house.Two neighborhood permit parking passes are provided for your stay.
host_about:
I am so excited to be able to share this fabulous home with you! I have traveled many places all around the world, and have always wanted to be a host. When traveling through India years ago, I had the unique pleasure of being hosted by families in their homes. It is a great way to experience an area, and adds so much to the memory.

I travel a lot for work and stay in many hotels. I know what makes for a comfortable and easy stay. I know you'll feel comfortable in my home.

I life live in the present and know that we are meant to be happy and experience joy.
