neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is 1 house per 50 acres so it has the country feel to it.  Two 3000 acres state parks,  Wilder Ranch and Grey Whale Ranch are in close proximity.   Our local, Wednesday Farmer's Market has abundant, organic produce, meat and eggs.  Also, nearby is the UCSC farm stand. We are 15 minutes from the North Coast Beaches, including the town of Davenport.  The Road House Restaurant in Davenport, Swanton Berry Farm Stand and U Pick are local favorites.  The Bonny Doon winery is often enjoyed by visitors.
notes: Please bring your own flashlight to help you navigate from the parking area to the house.  We do have solar lighting illuminating the pathways from the gate to the house. We have wonderful, natural spring water so bring your own water bottle to carry to town and on hikes.
transit: A car is essential for getting around from here unless you are an avid biker with your own bicycle.  The nearest bus stop is 2.5 miles from here.  Buses have the capacity to transport bicycles.

name: Big Blue Room+Priv Bath+Ocean View
summary: Views across Santa Cruz and the Pacific Ocean.  10' ceilings, douglas fir wood floors, comfortable queen on iron bed frame, antiques, + gas "wood stove".  Shower, toilet, sink. Relax and enjoy!
space: The Dake House as it is known in the Santa Cruz Historic Registry, was built in 1904 by Clarence Dake with the generous support of his wife’s family money. He was a gentleman farmer and started the first escrow/title business in Santa Cruz. The house sits on a hill overlooking the town of Santa Cruz, the mission and the sweeping views of the Monterey Bay and the Boardwalk. While High Street is centrally located of the main routes to UCSC, most of the 2/3 acre property is surrounded by nature. Red tail hawks soar and perch in the tall trees, deer regularly come by to graze, and the hummingbirds love all the salvias in the garden.  The ‘Blue Room” is large room with a firm,  comfortable queen bed on an iron frame.  Located on the second floor, on S/W side of the house, the room has 10’ coved ceilings, antique lighting, antique desk and dresser, a mini refrigerator in the closet, and a chair. The room has a small (and private) bathroom with a toilet, shower, and sink.   This is one bedroo

transit: Airport-We are about 40 minutes to San Jose International Airport (SJC). San Francisco Airport (SFO) is about 1 hour and 30 minutes without traffic. Los Angeles Airport (LAX) is about a 6 hour drive to the south using the fastest routes.  Train-Amtrak train is about 30 minutes away (in Salinas). You can take a connector bus from downtown Santa Cruz metro station.  Walking to Downtown: Go downhill (East) on High Street. Cross over Highway 1 bridge. Continue on High Street. Cross park diagonally. Cross at crosswalk and walk down hill on Water Street. The Clock Tower and Pacific Avenue are at the bottom of the hill. Downtown will be to your right.  Other walking destinations: it is about a 20 minute uphill walk through a residential neighborhood to get to the hiking trails of the Pogonip. I recommend going down High Street to Highland. space: Clean, cozy, quiet backyard cottage one block from the Pacific Avenue shopping and restaurant district, short walk to the Warriors arena, and a half-mile from the Beach Boardwalk, Main Beach and the Municipal Wharf. One bedroom detached cottage with a comfy queen foam-mattress bed and private bath with stand-up shower in a vintage claw-foot bathtub. Park in the driveway and stroll through the vegetable garden to your private little surf shack. A fold-out foam mattress is available for kids.  We're right downtown, so park your car for the weekend and walk to dozens of great shops, restaurants and music clubs. Take the Santa Cruz Trolley to the beach for twenty-five cents, rent a Segway or bike along scenic West Cliff Drive. We can direct you to beaches, parks, wineries, craft breweries, farmers markets, special events, music shows and great restaurants for every budget. Or just hang out in a lawn chair and read. We keep the cottage very clean to accommodate visitors with allergies, unfo
notes: Please note that there is no refrigerator and no cooking allowed in the cottage (other than the coffee maker). We ask guests to be very careful when snacking in the cottage, as crumbs and food scraps attract ants. It is best to snack outside, please feel free to use the patio tables and chairs for meals. Please do not rinse food scraps in the sink or bathtub, as they clog the plumbing. Please do not eat in bed, as food stains the linens. We don't use pesticides, and rely on cleanliness to keep the ants out in the yard where they belong. Please toss used food and drink containers in the trash cans in the driveway, and not in the wastebaskets in the cottage.  Thank you for helping us keep the cottage super-clean and insect-free.

summary: We are honored to treat you to Jasmine Garden Oasis—3 blocks from beaches. Jasmine Studio upstairs, Ginger & Peach Rooms downstairs. Set back from the street, our space is bright and clean surrounded by gardens--renewing for your heart, body & soul.
space: We are Marie & Peter, a married couple hosting you in our home located three blocks from the beach. Our three rooms offer either a queen bed (Jasmine Studio and Peach Room) or double futon bed (Ginger Room), with optional optional single temporary bed in each room, and 10% discount with each additional room you book. We are tucked away from the street near a lovely walk/bike path to the beach--no need to walk on a main street or take a car out into traffic. Our modest garden is serene and renewing . . . grass to sit in or do yoga . . . a rock waterfall . . . flowering plants, fruit trees and vines . . .porch and brick patios, hot tub . . . with an opportunity for you to receive massage or acupuncture right in your private room or in the garden by healing artists who live nearby.  We provide a healthy environment, use green and non-toxic products whenever possible, non-scented soaps and detergents. We are eco-friendly, use solar panels, hang dry clothes when possible, conserve water, an

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is a relatively quiet neighborhood with an assortment of people who enjoy living near the beach--including long-time residents, families, retired people, UCSC students, and surfers interspersed to keep it characteristic of Santa Cruz.  Two blocks away is a modest shopping center which hosts the local farmer's market on Sunday mornings. A handful of eateries and a coffee shop, from fast food to upscale dining, line the two blocks toward the beaches. A back way to the beach (our special secret) is three lovely blocks, two of which are walking/biking trails, one lined with Cypress trees, and the next along a lagoon lined with Eucalyptus trees. The Harbor and Crows Nest restaurant and nightclub are a several blocks to the west along the shore. Downtown Santa Cruz is 3 miles west and Capitola, a quaint seaside town, is 2 miles east. Both are easily accessible by bike lanes, public transportation and car.
notes: The Transient Occupancy tax for AirB&B rooms in Santa Cruz county is 11%. See below for details. We ask that you pay us in the blue envelope you will see on the desk when you arrive, either with a personal check or cash.  Our house has three AirBnB rooms, and sound travels in our home, so please be considerate of others during our quiet hours (9:00pm to 7:30am). Because we are a shoes-free home, slip-on slippers and slip-on garden shoes are handy to leave inside and outside the door. Check-in time is 3:00pm and check-out time is 11:00am. Feel free to leave luggage on the porch and make yourselves at home if you wish to arrive early or stay late. Santa Cruz area has been suffering a severe water shortage, and water is rationed. We have installed low flush toilets, we re-use grey water when possible, and we ask our guests to minimize their water usage.  NOTE: If you are interested in receiving massage, acupuncture, cranio-sacral therapy or Rolfing here, then message me and I will send yo
transit: Our location is very convenient for public transportation. The bus stop is around the corner that takes you directly to downtown Santa Cruz. The local bus service hooks up with service to San Jose, Caltrain, and all the Bay Area Transit systems including both San Jose and San Francisco Airports. From the airport, use Bay Area Transit system to Diridon Station in San Jose. From there you can catch the Hwy 17 Express to Santa Cruz. From the Santa Cruz downtown station take Santa Cruz Metro Bus 66 or 68 (Live Oak) to the bus stop nearest the intersection of 17th and Portola. The intersection is 2 blocks from our house. Car travel is convenient . . . street parking with no meters along our street. We use our carport as an unloading/loading zone for our guests' convenience. Bike travel is a dream with rentals accessible, bike lanes all through town, and longer bike trails in the area.
host_about: We, Peter & Marie, are a married couple who relish offering our sweet space & location to guests. We enjoy living in a tranquil atmosphere and want to share this with others of like mind at our home, Jasmine Garden Oasis near the Sea. It is a modest home tucked away in a modest neighborhood three blocks from the beach in east Santa Cruz with three B&B rooms--2 rooms downstairs with a shared bath and a private separate studio upstairs. We keep gentle gardens and cosy comfortable atmosphere for people who want a time of  renewal for body and soul. Mornings we visit the quiet beach to listen to the surf and watch the dawn, and evenings the dusk. We invite guests to join us for early morning yoga and/or meditation in our common room or on the lawn by the pond and waterfall. We have a list of massage therapists and acupuncturists who have offered to deliver their services to our guests in their private rooms. A lovely couple, Melissa and Rodney, are caretaking for us through Sept. 30 while we travel. We know you will enjoy their hosting in our home!

name: Ridgetop guesthouse with ocean view
summary: Private guesthouse on 9 acre property in the Santa Cruz mountains.  Gorgeous views across the mountains to the sea.  We are  30 minutes to town via narrow and hilly roads.  Not for those in a hurry! Wake up to hawks soaring outside your window.
space: Feels like Tuscany in the Santa Cruz mountains. There is one bedroom and one bathroom, outdoor space and a small kitchenette.  Our guest house is a completely separate two-floor structure from the main house, 692 square feet in total not including the outside area.  The kitchenette, eating area, bathroom and living room are located on the ground floor while the bedroom is on the tree house-like second floor.  Beautiful views from every room. neighborhood_overview: This neighborhood is known as the banana belt because it's the sunniest spot in Santa Cruz!  We are located in easy walking distance from several great local restaurants like the Crepe Place (best place to see live music most nights of the week) and Lillian's (Italian restaurant, extremely popular).   There's also great sushi (Akira) and Thai food (Real Thai-delivers!).  It's a 5 minute walk to the Buttery Bakery (amazing pastries, coffee, brunch) and to Shopper's Corner (best local market).  It's a quiet residential neighborhood without the seedy elements of Santa Cruz but still with quick and easy access to beaches, boardwalk and downtown.
notes: We are musicians and occasionally have band practice on the property.  We never play later than 9:30 and are generally not super loud. We have internet, but the wifi signal in the apartment is a little spotty at times.
transit: We are close to several bus lines.  It's very easy to get around on foot, by bike or by car.

host_about:

Terry grew up in CT  and has lived in Boulder, Manhattan  & SF. We are school teachers at a private school here.  As well, Terry has spent much of her working life as a food enthusiast and caterer (with the help of Clint) and she enjoys cooking fresh, healthy food from our farmer's markets.  We are passionate about the environment and do what we can to be living a green and sustainable life all around.  We love Santa Cruz and love to share it with people traveling through.   We welcome guests from around the globe  and we look forward to meeting new friends from different places.   We love traveling and getting lost in new cities and discovering their food specialties.  We also enjoy being in nature & by water, walking, music and life!  

This section is for Guests reading about us prior to submitting a Reservation Request:
• Airbnb is a trusted community marketplace with a mission to connect each Guest with an ideally matched Host. As a Guest, you can better your chances of an approval by posting a profile photo and a bit about yourself (and also who you are traveling with if that applies).
• As a guest, you of course would want to know as much about your host as possible to assure your safety and peace of mind. Additionally your host also wants to know about the people that will be sharing his/her home.
• We have never met and we know nothing about you so take a few moments to tell me who you are, what you like, what are your passions, hobbies etc.. No need to write a book just a few lines to give us a sense of who you are.
• To improve the chance of your request being accepted a complete profile is essential. A COMPLETE PROFILE includes a written statement about who you are, a recent photo of your face (no pets or children), and a verified email address and phone number. Doing these small things will increase the odds of an approved booking by tenfold. This is true for inquiries you make of any Host, not only us.
• VERIFY YOUR ID. You are going to be required to do this eventually, so do it now while you aren't pressed for time. It only takes a few minutes and it shows you value trust in our community. (See https://www.airbnb.com/help/question/450 for more information about Verified ID.)

neighborhood_overview: We hope our guests will enjoy all the amazing activities that Santa Cruz offers. You can walk, bike or drive a very short distance to everything you need. There are wonderful restaurants in the neighborhood. The Rio Theater is in walking distance, as well as a library, post office, supermarket, drugstore, natural grocery store, bakery, roller rink, and park. We are minutes from De La Veaga golf course, the Santa Cruz boat harbor, several beaches, and the Boardwalk.
notes: As a convenience to our guests, all rates include an 11% hotel tax, required by the City of Santa Cruz, and is not collected separately.
transit: There are buses within 4 blocks that take you downtown. There are restaurants, shops, and grocery stores within walking distance. Our neighborhood is literally in the center of Santa Cruz so it's incredibly easy to get around.
host_about: I'm an art teacher, world traveler, book lover, foodie, dancer, gardener and mother. I love raising my family in Santa Cruz. I feel blessed to live where the ocean meets the sea. I am excited to share my home with you!

summary: NEW on Airbnb!   Renovated craftsman home in the sunny "banana belt." Convenient access to beaches, trails, Beach Boardwalk, downtown, restaurants and everything Santa Cruz has to offer. Newbie discount includes 11% occupancy tax and cleaning fee.
space: Our frequent travels have made us appreciate that we have more room than we need so we decided to avail the front half of the house to guests.  We hope that it is inviting enough for your jaunts.   The front half is 600 sq ft, fully equipped and comfortably furnished.  When we are home and regrouping from our travels, we will be in the rear portion of the house.   A common wall, sliding door and utility room separate us, and we each have independent access.  You may hear and see us going through the driveway.  Think duplex:  so close, yet so far.

neighborhood_overview: We are a stone's throw away from local faves such as Charlie Hongkong, the Buttery, Shopper's Corner, Vivas, Rio Theatre, Crepe Place, Tacos Moreno, Lilian's and many others.  Around the corner are Whole Foods and Staff of Life.  It's fun, safe and convenient to ride our cruiser bikes to these places.   The Boardwalk, Wharf, Harbor and beaches are less than 2 miles away, as is the enticing hiking/biking trail/golf called Dela Veaga Park.  UCSC is a straight shot, less than 5 miles.  You see, midtown to everything!  We live in a quiet residential area and we like our neighbors.  We want them to continue liking us, too, so please be friendly when you meet them and please observe City ordinance noise laws.
notes: There is a fire hydrant in front of our house curb.  Although not painted red, you cannot park there :(.  Adjacent street parking is plentiful and when we are not onsite, you can use our driveway. Garbage pick-up is early Monday and can wake the dead!
transit: • There is plenty of safe street parking. • Quick access to Hwy 1. • Local bus lines are a block away • If you have a bike, bring it!
host_about:
Dane and I chose Santa Cruz as our home base because it offers the ocean, mountains and a strong community.  We love surfing although in our ripe age, we prefer the warm waters.   When landlocked, I lap swim, yoga and garden.  Dane hits the single tracks on his bike and tinkers with his car.  

Our travels have taken us to Asia, Europe, South and Central America.  Where have yours?  Come and share our home so we can exchange travel stories.

name: Santa Cruz Beach/Boardwalk Cottage
summary: Bright beach cottage on a typically quiet street w/ minimal traffic a short walk to Seabright Beach, great restaurants & the Boardwalk.  Fully equipped kitchen & landscaped backyard w/ BBQ and patio furniture perfect for outdoor dining.
space: The cottage has an open floor plan good for visiting and entertaining.  We love eating breakfast and lunch on the back patio in the rising sun and having a drink on the front porch in the setting sun.  The two queen beds and one full size sofa bed sleep six.  There is seating for six at the kitchen table.
description: Bright beach cottage on a typically quiet street w/ minimal traffic a short walk to Seabright Beach, great restaurants & the Boardwalk.  Fully equipped kitchen & landscaped backyard w/ BBQ and patio furniture perfect for outdoor dining.       The cottage has an open floor plan good for visiting and entertaining.  We love eating breakfast and lunch on the back patio in the rising sun and having a drink on the front porch in the setting sun.  The two queen beds and one full size sofa bed sleep six.  There is seating for six at the kitchen table.  At your own risk, feel free to use our two bicycles, four boogie boards, two skateboards and BBQ.  There are bookshelves full of board games, jigsaw puzzles, books, VHS movies, DVD movies and music CD's. The boombox will play the radio, a CD or an ipod with the large (old style) connector.  There are clock radios with alarms in each of the bedrooms.  Go ahead and use the jackets and umbrella hanging in the back bedroom if the weather turns.
neighborhood_overview: We love our neighborhood because it is on a street close to Seabright beach and the Boardwalk but there is little traffic and noise.  Parking is on the street and does not require a permit.  It is a short bike ride or a nice walk to downtown on the river path. The cottage is a short walk to Seabright Brewery (live music on Friday nights!), La Posta (one of our favorite restaurants), Seabright Beach, the Boardwalk and the San Lorenzo River path.
notes: There is a modem and wireless router for internet access at the cottage.   We don't have cable TV because we like to catch up on watching movies on DVD while we are there. There are Redbox kiosks at the nearby Safeway and 7-Eleven.  You can get some local channels using the converter box and antenna.   Because of the extreme Santa Cruz water shortage, please take short showers and use the on-off valve on the shower head to turn off the water when soaping up.  There is a washer and dryer but please only wash full loads on the shortest cycle.  We will take back to Fremont the sheets and towels to wash them.  If you have enough dirty dishes go ahead and run the dishwasher on its shortest cycle.  Keep the strainer in the kitchen drain and don't put anything down the sinks except for water.  Put food scraps in the compost not down the sink.
transit: There is a bus stop a couple short blocks away.  We primarily walk or ride our bikes when we are there.  The closest big airport is San Jose International which is about a half-hour drive (except during commute hours).
host_about: Barry is an engineering consultant and Holly is a retired teacher.  The Santa Cruz property is our second home and we only occasionally rent it out.  Rentals are limited to 7 nights per reservation.  We enjoy biking, hiking, surfing, snorkeling, fine dining, theatre, music and museums.  Enjoy at your own risk our onsite beach chairs, bikes, boogie boards and skateboards.

name: Modern Sunny 4BR Family Retreat
summary: Brand new remodel on a quiet street in upscale neighborhood. Beautiful sunny yard with lots of fruit trees. Downtown, Hiking,UCSC, Beach and Restaurants all within just 2-3 miles.
space: This is practically a brand new house, never lived in. We recently remodeled this 4 br house and hope that you will enjoy your stay. The master bedroom is located on the outer wing of the house and has a Cal King bed. The room has two closets and a private entrance to the back yard. The two other bedrooms are equipped with queen beds. The fourth bedroom has a twin size day bed with a fold out twin trundle.  The kitchen has an induction cooktop, microwave and oven.  The house has central heating, however the bathrooms are equipped with warm floors.  The spacious back yard is filled with seasonal fruit trees, please feel welcome to taste some of the fruit.  If you haven’t been to Santa Cruz, it's time for a visit- between the beaches, surfing, mountain biking, hiking, good music, and wine tasting (80 wineries in the Santa Cruz Mountains), and more, it makes for a perfect get-away.

neighborhood_overview: The house is located on a quiet street with two hour parking on the street and two parking spaces in front of the garage. Right around the corner is Westlake Park. A park with a little lake and a great playground. Kids can get their first fishing experience at the lake.  A short walk up the road will bring you to the entrance of the Pogonip, a natural preserve, with endless trails and beautiful views. We are less than ten minutes from all of the excitement at the Boardwalk (we like to ride our bikes, just coming back up the hill is a work out — takes about 15 minutes- this way we don’t have to pay for parking!). Downtown is brisk walk or a short 5 min. drive.  If you walk along West Cliff to the lighthouse you can watch the pro-surfers do their tricks at Steamers Lane. If you walk the other way on West Cliff you can visit the Monarch butterfly sanctuary at Natural Bridges State Park. We are a short ways away from the natural grocery store (New Leaf), Safeway, and many restaurants/ameni
notes: Please give us a short description about your party, how many children (ages) and adults. Please note, the house is not child proofed.  We would like you to complete your profile and be verified with Airbnb.  We do not allow pets.  At times we might have a large camper parked in the drive way. The camper is not occupied. If you need a later check out time, please talk to us.
transit: The public bus system is at the end of the street. It will take you across town. There is a ZipCar location nearby, if you are carless. Otherwise, Santa Cruz is a very bike friendly city and you can nearly bike anywhere (just bring a lock).
host_about:
I moved with my family from Palo Alto to Santa Cruz about two years ago and we absolutely love it here.  Santa Cruz is full of excitement and beauty, I feel I am on a vacation, every morning when I wake up. 
I am originally from Germany. I love traveling, meeting people and exploring new locations and cultures.  Every year, my brother and I will pick a place to visit, that neither of us have been to. However, my favorite city is still my home base, Hamburg in Germany.

space: Welcome to our bungalow at the beach!  If you are in the drive-way, you can access the beach by going left.  There are a number of beaches in the area.  One is sure to suit your purpose.  About the unit, it stays climate controlled most of the time.  Open the window for some fresh ocean air.  If you need heat, there is a riostat to the left of the small wall painting and we now have fans that do a great job of cooling the room on warmer days. neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood consists mostly of owner occupied homes, many of which  have had the same owners for 20 years or more. There are a few new homes that have been built over the past few years and even the smaller older homes are well kept and being a block from the beach maintain high values and pride of ownership.
notes: The Hook, which is one of Santa Cruz's best surf spots is in walking distance as are several great beaches in the area. Our October guests have a number of Pumpkin Patches within driving distance as well.  The Roaring Camp Railroad  is a great trip to take with children through the  Santa Cruz Redwood filled forest. The Tyrolean Inn has a great October fest in Felton less than a 1/2 hour drive away . The Chardonnay II is a 70 foot long ultralight sailing yacht that sails year round from Santa Cruz harbor offering sunset cruises, wine tasting, and whale watching along with a long list of other special cruises. Access The Chardonnay II on google for more details. The yacht harbor is only 5 minutes away from us. Hope to see you soon!
transit: As stated above there is covered parking for one vehicle and bus stops for local transportation are located on Portola Ave. which is a 10 minute walk toward the Capitola Mall.
host_about: Hi, Karen and Wilder here. We love our beach lifestyle and enjoy sharing it with others, including our two French Bulldogs, Lola and Napoleon.When not working, we enjoy the beach, sports, painting, exercising, and hanging out with friends and family. Its fun to stroll along East Cliff Dr, watching the surfers and marine life as we head to our destination. Capitola is loaded with fine restaurants,unique shops, and wine tasting . We take advantage of it all. We walk past the Hook to witness some of the best surfing on the West Coast. If we're in the mood for a movie or need to go to the Mall its a short walk in the other direction. Take in the sunset at the end of our street where you can also see Steamers Lane, the Boardwalk, and Monterey across the bay.We welcome you to join us and experience the beauty of this special place.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood offers wide streets with plenty of parking, pleasant walks with interesting architecture and diverse plant life. With the ocean just four blocks away, and more than one local state park, we welcome lots of nature lovers. We have quite a few families visit - sometimes even three generations of fun-loving folks. We also have couples come for romantic getaways, and groups of friends visit for surfing, biking, and jogging along West Cliff. Some people come just to go to the beach, and others for work. Some people come to get away from the heat of the valley, and others for the sweet, temperate sunshine.
notes: Santa Cruz has a 10pm city-wide quiet ordinance. Artisan Beach House is in a peaceful family neighborhood that respects this ordinance, and we welcome you to join us if you feel this is a match to your vacation style. If you prefer the louder, later style of vacation, we ask you that you respect our neighbors, and find a rental better suited for your vacation.

But when you are sipping tea or a beer on the porch, you'll hear nothing but the hummingbirds and the wind in the trees. We have two bedrooms for rent in our home. neighborhood_overview: Bonny Doon is a charming community in the mountains, blending serious old-timers with vacation-home implants, and intentionally keeping itself "rural and natural." The people here consciously cultivate a sense of community and are genuinely friendly. The beauty of the Santa Cruz mountains is phenomenal. Our home is centrally located between several state parks: Big Basin, Henry Cowell (to which we are adjacent), Wilder Ranch and Waddell Beach. The beach town of Davenport is fifteen minutes away, and boasts a good restaurant (the Roadhouse), a locally-famous cafe/bakery (the Whale City), frequent live music, and a sprinkling of shops, all with Pacific views. The mountain towns of Felton, Ben Lomond, and Boulder Creek area also nearby and quaint. Nearby Santa Cruz is full of charms that include and transcend its tourist-spot reputation! Don't miss going to the beach - the boardwalk for tourist tradition, or colorful Capitola, or one of many secluded coves. Enjoy the chic Pacific Avenue M
notes: We do charge 20 extra per person over 2 people, including babies and children. Please check with us if you plan on bringing a young child, as the wall between the two rooms is thin and we want all our guests to have a good experience!
transit: The bus line runs on Empire Grade just a quarter mile away down a private road, and you are welcome to investigate it. Having private transport is highly recommended, though. Parking is simple and abundant. The nearest airport is Monterey, which is quite nice, though it's small - SFO is just over an hour away. Rental cars are abundantly available there.
host_about:
Hi there! I'm a friendly and thoughtful person who loves being outdoors and enjoys making things. The varieties of human experience are fascinating to me - I'm an anthropology graduate student and avid reader. I delight in gardening, good food, and spending time with my sweet huge horse. 

As a host, my partner Karim and I are cheerful and warm, happy either to get to know you or to give you space, whichever you're in the mood for. Enjoy privacy on the deck for your morning tea, sit with us by the fire and share a glass of wine and travel stories, gather up tips for all the good spots to eat and play nearby. We have lived all over the Bay Area and know it well - I am a native Californian and Karim is a charming French transplant. We share our home with a delightful dog who is extremely mellow and friendly with people - he's a medium size English Setter / Australian Shepherd mix - and a grey cat who loves to be pet. Between us, we have traveled to over 30 countries and have lived in Germany, Ghana, Italy, and Sweden.

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is a relatively quiet neighborhood with an assortment of people who enjoy living near the beach--including long-time residents, families, retired people, UCSC students, and surfers interspersed to keep it characteristic of Santa Cruz.  Two blocks away is a modest shopping center which hosts the local farmer's market on Sunday mornings. A handful of eateries and a coffee shop, from fast food to upscale dining, line the two blocks toward the beaches. A back way to the beach (our special secret) is three lovely blocks, two of which are walking/biking trails, one lined with Cypress trees, and the next along a lagoon lined with Eucalyptus trees. The Harbor and Crows Nest restaurant and nightclub are a several blocks to the west along the shore. Downtown Santa Cruz is 3 miles west and Capitola, a quaint seaside town, is 2 miles east. Both are easily accessible by bike lanes, public transportation and car.
notes: The Transient Occupancy tax for AirB&B rooms in Santa Cruz county is 11%. See below for details. We ask that you pay us in the blue envelope you will see on the desk when you arrive, either with a personal check or cash.  Our house has three AirBnB rooms, and sound travels in our home, so please be considerate of others during our quiet hours (9:00pm to 7:30am). Because we are a shoes-free home, slip-on slippers and slip-on garden shoes are handy to leave inside and outside the door. Check-in time is 3:00pm and check-out time is 11:00am. Feel free to leave luggage on the porch and make yourselves at home if you wish to arrive early or stay late. Santa Cruz area has been suffering a severe water shortage, and water is rationed. We have installed low flush toilets, we re-use grey water when possible, and we ask our guests to minimize their water usage.  NOTE: If you are interested in receiving massage, acupuncture, cranio-sacral therapy or Rolfing here, then message me and I will send yo
transit: Our location is very convenient for public transportation. The bus stop is around the corner that takes you directly to downtown Santa Cruz. The local bus service hooks up with service to San Jose, Caltrain, and all the Bay Area Transit systems including both San Jose and San Francisco Airports. From the airport, use Bay Area Transit system to Diridon Station in San Jose. From there you can catch the Hwy 17 Express to Santa Cruz. From the Santa Cruz downtown station take Santa Cruz Metro Bus 66 or 68 (Live Oak) to the bus stop nearest the intersection of 17th and Portola. The intersection is 2 blocks from our house. Car travel is convenient . . . street parking with no meters along our street. We use our carport as an unloading/loading zone for our guests' convenience. Bike travel is a dream with rentals accessible, bike lanes all through town, and longer bike trails in the area.
host_about: We, Peter & Marie, are a married couple who relish offering our sweet space & location to guests. We enjoy living in a tranquil atmosphere and want to share this with others of like mind at our home, Jasmine Garden Oasis near the Sea. It is a modest home tucked away in a modest neighborhood three blocks from the beach in east Santa Cruz with three B&B rooms--2 rooms downstairs with a shared bath and a private separate studio upstairs. We keep gentle gardens and cosy comfortable atmosphere for people who want a time of  renewal for body and soul. Mornings we visit the quiet beach to listen to the surf and watch the dawn, and evenings the dusk. We invite guests to join us for early morning yoga and/or meditation in our common room or on the lawn by the pond and waterfall. We have a list of massage therapists and acupuncturists who have offered to deliver their services to our guests in their private rooms. A lovely couple, Melissa and Rodney, are caretaking for us through Sept. 30 while we travel. We know you will enjoy their hosting in our home!

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is comprised of fairly young people. The empty lot immediately adjacent to the creek and the driveway was once the epicenter and final party place of the famed pleasure point bike race - however, since the last residents moved out the home has since been torn down and the party is held in another part of the neighborhood. Its now an awesome, make-shift dog park and if you have a doggie, Im sure they will find it full of smells of the neighborhood dogs. The beach is literally 3 blocks down the road and the sunset walks a must for everyone on the block - we all grab a glass of wine and head down to the cliffs with doggies in tow. We have a very loving, communal group of neighbors and we all watch out for one another.
notes: I have a large German Pointer named Richard Rex, he is a 10 year old, lovable family dog that might bark - but he is confined to the front yard at all times. Unless you want to make friends. I have two - three old beach cruisers that are available for you use, however, they are old and rickety - renting beach cruisers is always convenient and I can provide any gear outfitters you may fancy - just let me know what your interests are before you arrive and I can compile a short list.
transit: Everything is fairly close to the house. Bus transportation, rental car facilities, bike rental, surf shops, 41st avenue & Pleasure Point business' and cafes are all a short walk if not a extremely short bike ride.

neighborhood_overview: We live on a dead end street. We know all of our neighbors and we look out for each other.  We feel strongly in this day and age, it is important to know and engage with each other. We are a bike ride away from downtown and the historical Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk.  We are also only a short distance to some of the best mountain bike areas California has to offer!  We are one mile to the closest beach and two miles from the redwoods.      Santa Cuz is known for its surfing, road and mountain biking, Monterey Bay sea life, artist community, sustainable and organic cuisine, and a laid back, yet responsible way of life.  We hope you will come visit and fall in love with Santa Cruz like we have!
notes: Keith and I are avid travelers.  We know what it takes to make our guests feel welcome and comfortable.   I am a lover of the arts, food and flea marketing.  I recently returned from a solo vacation to Europe, where I used Airbnb the entire time. Keith is an active outdoor sportsman who is willing to show you the best bike/nature trails in the area.  He is even willing to tag along if you'd like.  Keith has been all over the globe and has participated in natural disaster relief. We are recent empty nesters, who are beginning a new chapter in life.  We look forward to what is in store as we share our home with you.  We have 2  non-allergenic "Mutt-Doodles" Murphy and Junior. They are lovable, silly and will do their best to get a rub or two from you.
transit: We have a bus stop at the end of our street that will take you to downtown Santa Cruz and beyond.  If interested, we have vintage Schwinn bikes we can lend you to cruise around town.  We are conveniently located near the famous California Coastal Highway 1.

I am originally from NY (but have lived in Ca. for many years)
Keith was born and raised in the Bay Area. 
We have 2 kids , the youngest just left for college.
We love to travel whether it is in our state, our country or across the seas!
We love all forms of art and music.
We know Santa Cruz inside and out and look forward to showing you some of our favorite spots.
We look forward to sharing our comfy new Empty Nest with you.

host_about: I come from a french background and grew up in a family owning hotel, bed and breakfast and restaurant in France. I have been the host of many travelers from all over the world since then, because I believe in sharing experiences, differences and I want to open up my place to the world. I have a green home, where I am mindful of electrical usage and water usage (be aware of the drought)! I am a foodie,   I grow my vegetables. I am always looking for more ideas and new tips to do things yourself. When you come to visit I will give you a tour of my place. I like to share my knowledge and find out about yours.

neighborhood_overview: The villa is located one block from the ocean and scenic West Cliff Drive. There are are several great beaches, quiet hidden coves and scenic bay views within minutes of your front door. Hop on one of our bikes to explore the neighborhood. You can shop for fresh produce at the farmer’s market, sample a pint at a local brewery, get buzzed on caffeine or taste a flight of fantastic wine.  With 29 beaches surrounding the city, Santa Cruz is famous for world-class waves and cliff walks. Go beyond the beach to find miles of forested mountain bike trails, a top research University, you-pick organic farms and coffee shops brimming with hipsters, hippies and entrepreneurs.
notes: We are opening on November first. That's why the price is low. Take advantage of it!
transit: Santa Cruz is easy to get around by bike or car. There is free parking in front of the Villa and you can rent a house bike and get downtown in 10 minutes.  - 1h20 min from San Francisco International Airport  - 40 min from San Jose Airport.  - Airport picks up and drop off can be organized. - Try using Skyscanner when you select your travel dates.  (If you live in the Bay area and don’t have a car, you can either take the Greyhound bus or the Cal train to San Jose, then catch the highway 17 bus to downtown Santa Cruz). THE SCENIC ROUTE TO & FROM SF: Take the slightly slower scenic route along the "Slow Coast" from Pacifica past Half Moon Bay, through Pescadero and Davenport. Be sure to check out the surf along the way and grab a few tacos at the Gas Station in Pescadero (Mercado & Taqueria De Amigos).
host_about: I am Emmanuel.. A 30 years old belgian guy that relocated in the bay area 2 years ago. I work in the online travel industry and travels a lot for my job. It's large beach house with an attached coworking space. We welcome entrepreneurs, freelancers, writers, business travellers that share a love for the ocean!

neighborhood_overview: Our Seabright neighborhood is a very quiet residential area. We have a small park 1/2 block away from our home, great for kids, and pups! ...and are walking distance to everything!!! We are only 1 mile to the harbor, Seabright beach, the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk, and UCSC. Arana Gulch, a 40 acre open space is only blocks away, walk it or ride on the bike path, over to the Harbor, Crows Nest, the beach! FUN! We've got an assortment of healthy grocery stores within walking distance, and lots of yummy restaurants. The Buttery (yum!) is within a mile away, as is the Seabright brewery, Akira sushi (3 blocks away!)La Posta Italian restaurant, Linda's Seabreeze Cafe (breakfast/lunch..get there early), ..the list goes on... You're nestled in a Redwood Mountain Valley with a stream that floes in the Winter, yet the home is situated in an open meadow with lots of light and views all around of the valley forest. Redwood Drive is just that, a 2.5 mile long drive, one lane-ish mountain road with a cul-de-sac. It's very safe, "over the top" peaceful easy living where you can go walking or biking or just hang out.
notes: The Redwood House is exceptional in that although it is in the Santa Cruz Mountains, unlike other valley, canyon or remote locations that don't open up to daylight or a have a view because of the forests, this location is naturally open, airy, light and spacious with great views of the hills and on a clear evening, our beautiful Monterrey Bay starry night sky.

host_about:
My love of food, cooking, wine and art has lead me on a lifelong journey. Years ago, I was a restauranteur in Chicago, then a full time studio potter, then a career in corporate sales and marketing.

I've traveled extensively, usually on a quest to find indigenous, traditional regional foods. Desert beans in India, grilled squid from a street vendor in Hong Kong, fresh rambutan in Thailand, black mole in Mexico, and hay soup in Austria are just a few memorable tastes. I am inspired by these experiences and I cook with international flavors.

A few years ago, I began to dream about having a farm where I could produce more of the foods, meats, and wines that I love. That dream came true when we bought FlipJack Ranch. Ranch life suits me, waking up to gather fresh eggs, cuddling the baby chicks, wrangling the goats, walking out to see the wooly pigs with a cup of coffee in hand. The whole 'farm to table' thing is real here on the ranch and the sustainable, organic and free range food products are my inspiration for daily menus. I love to forage too, here or nearby,  bringing back mushrooms, salad greens or mussels for the table. 

As a traveler myself, I value warm hospitality and those little things that make a stay memorable. I love it when I can go to a place and just unwind, assured that everything is there and I can just relax. I hope to make your stay with us memorable.

The comfy queen bed makes this space perfect for two.  Come stay at this lovely bungalow for an unforgettable Santa Cruz vacation. You'll enjoy: Wifi internet Cable TV and a DVD player beach cruiser bikes beach chairs and towels Linens and towels Soap and shampoo, a blow dryer Coffeemaker, teakettle, toaster Microwave Gas BBQ grill This is your own private hideaway. name: Ricketts' Retreat
summary: Cozy And Private Beach Bungalow, Hot Tub, Dog Friendly, 3 Short Blocks To Beach.
space: Named after local Marine Biologist, Edward F. Ricketts, the Ricketts' Retreat House has a classy Monterey Bay feel with an enclosed private yard, hundred-year old Monterey Cyprus tree, and naturally, you can see the ocean from the driveway.  In 3 blocks, you could be at the fire-pits of Twin Lakes Beach, sailing a boat at the Harbor, or grabbing a bite to eat at the Crow's Nest or Cafe El Palomar. In one mile, you could be riding the Giant Dipper at the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk.  Additionally, the famed Steamer Lane surf spot, West Cliff, Capitola, and UC Santa Cruz's Seymour Marine Discovery Center  are within a  four-mile radius of the house. The House is furnished in good taste with all essential amenities including linens, towels, and paper products.  The bedroom has a comfortable queen bed, desk, dresser, closet, adjoining bright bathroom (with windows) and walk-in shower. neighborhood_overview: Our spacious downtown vacation home is great for any occasion-- whether you want to spend a few days at the beach with your family, go hiking in the beautiful redwood forests our town has to offer, ride the Giant Dipper and enjoy a funnel cake at the Boardwalk, see the monarch butterflies nest at Natural Bridges State Park, have the perfect weekend getaway with your special someone, get a seafood dinner with an ocean view on the wharf, take a stroll down the beautiful backdrop of West Cliff Dr., or would just like enjoy some peace and quiet in a serene environment-- you've come to the right place! Walk to the farmers market  on Wednesdays and make yourself a gourmet meal in the large fully equipped kitchen. Everything we mentioned is in walking distance, you wouldn't even need to rent a car! The home is located in the heart of downtown Santa Cruz, but you wouldn't even know it! So peaceful and serene, it is extremely quiet, so much so, if you listen hard enough you can sometimes hear t
notes: Per Santa Cruz City law, we are required as Airbnb hosts to collect the Transient Occupancy Tax (TOT) separately from your Airbnb transaction. The TOT is 11% of the nightly rate (before fees) for each night you stay. As this is a city tax, we are not allowed to collect this through Airbnb. We will collect this in cash or check upon check-in or during checkout. Check in is at 4PM  **********************  Check out is at 11AM  **********************  For guests that are planning on going to The Boardwalk:  Consider staying with us on a Monday or a Tuesday, as the Boardwalk has 1.00 rides, hot dogs, cotton candy & soda from 5PM to closing. It's a great bargain and tons of fun!  The house is separated into two different units, an upstairs and a downstairs. They are completely private from each other, with two separate entrances on either side of the house, and a door that connects to the farthest bedroom that connects the two units that will remain locked at all times. There is a chance t
transit: Walking and biking is the best way to appreciate the Santa Cruz scenery.  However, car rental services are available. There is a bus station on Pacific Ave. but there are many bus stops closer to your home away from home. The Metro Bus Station is where both local buses and Greyhound buses depart from. The Santa Cruz Trolley loops around Pacific Ave. and goes to the wharf and Boardwalk for only 25 cents! You can rent segway scooters down the street from the Boardwalk to use in that area. Information regarding rental services will be included in our information pamphlet, or emailed upon request. 1 guest pass is available for the permitted street parking. A link to the Santa Cruz parking map is available upon request. We're only a phone call away to answer any of your getting-around questions or to give directions. The Santa Cruz Information booth on Pacific Ave. is very informative and helpful as well.
host_about:
Hello, we're Rex and Briana Solway! We have both lived in Santa Cruz our entire lives, and know the town like the back of our hand(s). We enjoy traveling, fine dining, photography, and the ocean-- we wouldn't be able to live far from the beach! We're avid sushi lovers, die hard Survivor fans, adore cats (but no worries if you have allergies, no kitties live here!), and often find ourselves critiquing the films and shows we watch. We worship the sun, but thrive under the moon and the stars when it's dark outside. We're always looking for the next adventure that awaits around the corner. 

We're dedicated to providing the best possible experience for you and your family, and will create a unique experience you'll never forget!

neighborhood_overview: Friendly and quiet neighborhood right in the heart of the Banana Belt, we are in a convenient location for getting around. We are literally a 2 minute drive to De Laviega golf course and Frisbee golf, just about a 10 minute drive to downtown, most beaches, the harbor and the Boardwalk (all about 1.5-2 miles from our house). Santa Cruz is a great place to bring your bikes and our garage is very secure to lock them in.
notes: We do have a small dog, Elle, who will most likely greet you with a welcoming bark or two (or ten), but she will remain quiet once youv'e settled in. She spends her the time in our house with our cat Olive. Things to note:  •The oven and stove work great but please do not heat above 400 degrees or use the broiler if possible. The smoke alarm in the kitchen is very sensitive. If the smoke alarm goes off because of the oven just open some windows and it should stop shortly. Running the fan above the stove helps.  •Spices and ironing board are on either side of the fridge. Iron and blow dryer in closet. •Although we believe we have a very safe neighborhood, as a general precaution when parking on the street, please keep any valuables hidden from the street view.  •We have a Culligan water filtration system, water taste great right from the tap. •We have space in our garage for a couple of bikes or surfboards. •Sorry but the backyard is not for Airbnb guests.   •Since we usually get up ear
transit: Biking or driving is convenient and easy from where we live. Uber and taxis are about a 10-15 to get to The Boardwalk or downtown (depending on the time of day).
host_about: We've lived in Santa Cruz for over 20 years. We like to travel, listen to music (especially live!), hike, bike ride, and are happy living in one of the best cities in the world. We love our home and are excited to share it with you!

neighborhood_overview: This is a well cared for space in a great neighborhood, half a mile from UCSC and walking distance to downtown. I am happy to say the neighbors are all really friendly and we often stop to visit with each other. There is a coffee shop just around the corner called The Abbey, which is a great meeting place. Also close to Hwy 1 (Mission St) and Hwy 17 and 1.5 miles from Cowell Beach where you can surf, rent kayaks, or just walk along beautiful West Cliff Drive ..and 3.6 miles from Upper Wilder Ranch and amazing mountain bike trails. The down hill traffic from UCSC can back up in front of the house as they wait to get onto Hwy 1. This usually occurs in the afternoon and doesn't last that long. The traffic in Santa Cruz in general has gotten a lot heavier in the afternoons everywhere. Since my house is very central, I do a lot of walking and biking. The walk to downtown is literally six blocks and highly recommended. Ask me for walking directions!
notes: The master bedroom and bath are large. The room is approximately 15' x 15' with a large desk and a smaller pull out sofa.  The second bedroom is much smaller than the master, still very very nice. The room is 8'x9' and has a large operable skylight as opposed to a window.  It has it's own bathroom with shower that is attached to it. There is a door separating the bedroom and bathroom.
transit: Bus stops are located within a block. Three zip car locations are within several blocks. Bike riding is ideal and as I mentioned walking downtown is pretty easy.

neighborhood_overview: Many people who have visited say they are surprised by what they see when they walk through our gate- it's not what they expected from the outside (a mixture of single story older homes- like ours, newer 2 story homes, attractive condos, and a mobile home park across the street). The stone entry path is edged by bamboo, a fountain, and plants that evoke a lush, tropical feeling. Though we have easy access to the freeway, it feels like you're far from the busy-ness of city life.  Our neighborhood is diverse in income levels and cultural backgrounds and is at the edge of a riparian corridor, so it has a little bit of wilderness even though it's in the middle of town. On our street are a nursery, a friendly auto mechanic, and a house with horses. It feels somewhat rural, even though we have such easy access to many parts of town. We are close enough to ride a bike to the ocean in about 15 minutes, but are also close to nice hiking trails in the mountains with redwoods and streams. Within
notes: We will provide  tea or coffee with fruit, granola, and yogurt in the morning.  We have a small dog and a cat who live in the house. My daughter's dog, Pickle, stays with us sometimes. He barks when new people come, but quiets down quickly if you don't reach down to pet him or give him too much attention. He can be very sweet and loves to play once he's assured you're okay.
transit: A major bus line is located about 5 blocks from our house. You can walk to 41st Ave. in less than 15 minutes where there are coffee shops, a mall, and restaurants. The best way to get here from the airport is to rent a car, take the bus (easier from San Jose, more challenging from SFO), or hire an airport shuttle service (available for 40-100). This is a wonderful location for bike riding! Bike rentals are available nearby, and we have two bikes available for loan- a cruiser and a 3 speed. They're not the most beautiful, but they work!
host_about:
Five things I can't live without.... farmer's markets, 4-legged furry creatures that like to snuggle and sit on my lap, birds singing in my garden, my bicycle, time with my kids. I would also say living by the ocean, but I suppose I could live near a river, lake, or stream in the mountains as long as I make regular treks to the ocean!

I am a high school teacher and live with my partner, Dan, who is a builder in Santa Cruz County. My daughter (in her 20s) is also temporarily living with us. I have lived in Santa Cruz since 1980 and Dan grew up in the area. We love spending time in nature: hiking, biking, kayaking, and paddleboarding. Interests include salsa rueda dancing, local history, marine life, traditional plant uses, permaculture, cooking, gardening, and observing the many species of birds in our backyard. Dan has surfed here for decades, so can advise good surf spots. He also knows of a fun archery range in the redwoods nearby. We love showing people around our area! We strive to be conscientious of our environment and are excited that our home is now powered by solar panels!!

I have traveled to many places, including Mexico, Jamaica, Ecuador, Bali, Java, Singapore, Thailand, Malaysia, Costa Rica, Belize, Hong Kong, Taiwan, the Philippines, Norway, Greece, Turkey, and Tanzania. I recently climbed Mt. Kilimanjaro with my daughter- the hardest thing I've ever done. Of course, a safari in the Serengeti was a childhood dream that was also fulfilled on that trip. Camping and cross country skiing are favorite things to do in the Sierra Nevada Mountains, where I go several times a year. I have driven across the United States 4 times (when gas was cheaper and before my understanding of global climate change issues) and was able to visit many of our National Parks, like Yosemite, Yellowstone, Death Valley, and the Grand Canyon. When I visit another culture, I love to immerse myself by learning some of the language, eating local food, and exploring the history and social background. I prefer staying at hostels or homestays over big hotels. A little adventure, time in nature, and physical activity are always important to me. 

I grew up in Illinois- until I was 14, when I moved to California to live with my mother. My mother is the 10th woman to solo circumnavigate the world and now lives in Mexico, so I've spent quite a bit of time sailing and living on boats. Now I prefer a kayak or paddleboarding, as they give more opportunities for observing wildlife. I once worked as a crewmember on a whalewatching boat. I've also been a veterinary aide, exotic animal caretaker, stained glass artist, and a docent in the state parks. 

My favorite part about hosting air bnb guests is discovering how much we have in common. I am inspired to know there are so many people out there from all parts of the world who are thoughtful, fun, interesting, and with a good sense of humor- and who share my passion about caring for this amazing planet we call home. It's so fun to share ideas- I've gotten many helpful tips from guests on how to live more sustainably. The biggest surprise was a guest who had an aunt that was my neighbor and shared a driveway with me for 5 years!

It is a two block walk to town,  the beach and the marina, restaurants, shops, grocery stores and art galleries. It is a two block walk to the entry to the Tahoe Rim hiking trail. The Rim Trail runs for over one hundred miles around the lake with several entry points. The closest is two blocks from the cabin.

host_about:
My love of food, cooking, wine and art has lead me on a lifelong journey. Years ago, I was a restauranteur in Chicago, then a full time studio potter, then a career in corporate sales and marketing.

I've traveled extensively, usually on a quest to find indigenous, traditional regional foods. Desert beans in India, grilled squid from a street vendor in Hong Kong, fresh rambutan in Thailand, black mole in Mexico, and hay soup in Austria are just a few memorable tastes. I am inspired by these experiences and I cook with international flavors.

A few years ago, I began to dream about having a farm where I could produce more of the foods, meats, and wines that I love. That dream came true when we bought FlipJack Ranch. Ranch life suits me, waking up to gather fresh eggs, cuddling the baby chicks, wrangling the goats, walking out to see the wooly pigs with a cup of coffee in hand. The whole 'farm to table' thing is real here on the ranch and the sustainable, organic and free range food products are my inspiration for daily menus. I love to forage too, here or nearby,  bringing back mushrooms, salad greens or mussels for the table. 

As a traveler myself, I value warm hospitality and those little things that make a stay memorable. I love it when I can go to a place and just unwind, assured that everything is there and I can just relax. I hope to make your stay with us memorable.

neighborhood_overview: 'Westside Wonderful' is located in 'The Circles' in Westside Santa Cruz. It has an interesting history: "The Circles is largely considered a “marvelous planning disaster” by the architecturally minded. It was developed in a haphazard fashion. Tent homes made of plywood and canvas were common in the early years. The circle pattern also resulted in many odd and substandard-sized lots; many are between 2,000 and 3,000 square feet, while a standard city lot is (phone number hidden). Today you will see many large houses with strange angles crammed into these tiny lots. That said, the neighborhood does have a more cohesive feel than many. It still has a local market and a distinctive laid back and friendly atmosphere; a good thing since it’s so easy to get turned around!"
notes: We have two small dogs: Reina (a white Lhasa/Terrier mix---sweetest dog ever,) and Hopper (a long-haired dachshund who is more like Eeyore!) If they happen to be outside, they will bark to greet you, but do not be alarmed---just come on through the gate and you will become their new best friend within 5 seconds. The city of Santa Cruz levies an 11% Transient Occupancy Tax that is included in the price, which we then give to the city. Santa Cruz City TOT Registration Certificate #738-955.
transit: There is a greenbelt that provides a pleasant six block walk to the ocean, at West Cliff Drive, and as noted there are several cafes, bakeries, wineries, breweries and restaurants within walking distance (10 minutes) or a very short drive. It's 1.5 miles to downtown Santa Cruz's Pacific Avenue, so again a short drive, or a 30-minute walk. The Bus Stop to take the Number 20 bus to the Beach Boardwalk and downtown, or to Natural Bridges State Park and the UC Santa Cruz campus is just two blocks away.

We moved to Santa Cruz in July 2011 from Chicago.  It's been quite a culture shift; but we love it, we love the relaxed and friendly culture of Santa Cruz, we really think there's no place like it and we have traveled all over the world.   We've traveled to 42 countries together and have a passion for social justice issues; both globally and locally.  Chad recently founded ruly, a social impact company focused on job creation for women in developing economies.  Jodi works as a psychotherapist at UCSC's Counseling & Psychological Services.  Our boys (ages 8 and 9) love living in Santa Cruz; boogie boarding at Cowell's, [playing soccer at Depot Park, or mountain biking at Wilder Ranch.

This listing is for our Primary Residence, which we rent when we travel throughout the year.  Grandparents and extended family are in Michigan, so we spend a lot of time traveling away from Santa Cruz to visit family or to visit more places around the globe!
